WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:03.754
Hi, guys. Um, I am Tom Holland.

00:03.837 --> 00:07.007
I'm joined today by Tobey Maguire
and Andrew Garfield.

00:07.090 --> 00:10.594
We just wanted to take a moment
to say a massive thank you

00:10.677 --> 00:13.263
for all of your continued love
and support for this film.

00:13.347 --> 00:16.433
While we were making this film,
I think I can speak on behalf of all of us

00:16.517 --> 00:19.478
that we knew that we had our hands
on something really special.

00:19.561 --> 00:21.563
But I don't think
we could ever have imagined

00:21.647 --> 00:23.774
it would have been received
as well as it has been.

00:23.857 --> 00:25.567
So thank you so much.

00:25.651 --> 00:29.154
We are just incredibly grateful
that you guys are here for it.

00:29.238 --> 00:31.949
Thank you to everybody
for supporting this movie.

00:32.031 --> 00:36.787
I got to show up with these guys
and have a beautiful experience.

00:36.870 --> 00:39.665
-Andrew, we have something to tell you.
-What?

00:39.748 --> 00:42.876
It's important to both of us
that you know this. Okay?

00:43.919 --> 00:45.045
-We love you.
-We love you.

00:45.754 --> 00:48.173
About time. I've been waiting months.

00:48.257 --> 00:50.676
I've been waiting months
since that day in Atlanta.

00:50.759 --> 00:52.094
-I had it in here.
-Yeah.

00:52.177 --> 00:54.638
It took every part of me not to say that.

00:54.721 --> 00:56.098
This was worth the wait,

00:56.181 --> 00:59.643
and I will wait for you guys
for centuries.

01:02.646 --> 01:04.605
<i>We come to you
now with revelations</i>

01:04.690 --> 01:07.860
<i>about last week's attack in London.
An anonymous source provided this video.</i>

01:07.943 --> 01:12.739
<i>It shows Quentin Beck, aka Mysterio,
moments before his death.</i>

01:12.823 --> 01:14.741
<i>You may find this video disturbing.</i>

01:14.825 --> 01:17.327
<i>I managed to send the Elemental
back through the rift,</i>

01:17.411 --> 01:19.621
<i>but I don't think
I'm gonna make it off this bridge alive.</i>

01:19.705 --> 01:20.873
<i>Spider-Man attacked me.</i>

01:20.956 --> 01:23.458
<i>He has an army of drones,
Stark technology.</i>

01:23.542 --> 01:27.212
<i>He's saying he's the only one who's
gonna be the new Iron Man. No one else.</i>

01:27.296 --> 01:29.548
<i>Are you sure you want
to commence the drone attack?</i>

01:29.631 --> 01:31.508
<i>There will be significant casualties.</i>

01:31.592 --> 01:33.552
<i>Do it. Execute them all.</i>

01:37.764 --> 01:40.809
<i>This shocking video
was released earlier today</i>

01:40.893 --> 01:43.896
<i>on the controversial news website
TheDailyBugle.net.</i>

01:43.979 --> 01:46.273
<i> There you have it, folks:
Conclusive proof</i>

01:46.356 --> 01:50.319
<i>that Spider-Man was responsible
for the brutal murder of Mysterio,</i>

01:50.402 --> 01:53.822
<i>an interdimensional warrior
who gave his life to protect our planet</i>

01:53.906 --> 01:59.453
<i>and who will, no doubt, go down in history
as the greatest superhero of all time.</i>

02:00.204 --> 02:01.747
<i>But that's not all, folks.</i>

02:01.830 --> 02:03.248
<i>Here's the real blockbuster.</i>

02:03.332 --> 02:05.042
<i>Brace yourselves.
You might wanna sit down.</i>

02:05.125 --> 02:07.419
<i>Spider-Man's real--
Spider-Man's real name is--</i>

02:09.545 --> 02:12.591
<i>Spider-Man's name is Peter Parker.</i>

02:13.467 --> 02:15.010
What the f--?

02:15.093 --> 02:17.846
<i>That's right, folks. Peter Parker.</i>

02:17.930 --> 02:20.724
<i>A 17-year-old high school delinquent...</i>

02:20.807 --> 02:23.477
- She knows him.
- Are you Spider-Man's girlfriend?

02:23.560 --> 02:25.020
<i>...is, in fact...</i>

02:25.103 --> 02:28.315
-Are you Spider-Man's girlfriend?
<i>-...the vile vigilante villain Spider-Man.</i>

02:28.398 --> 02:30.317
- Yo, it's him.
- Whoa, whoa.

02:30.400 --> 02:32.569
-Please don't touch her.
-You're just a kid?

02:32.653 --> 02:34.071
You murdered Mysterio?

02:34.154 --> 02:35.781
- You helped him?
- I didn't--

02:35.864 --> 02:37.950
Come on, kid, let me see your face.

02:38.033 --> 02:39.785
-He hit me. Spider-Man hit me.
-Come on.

02:39.868 --> 02:40.702
He hit me.

02:40.786 --> 02:44.289
<i>All this time, people looked up
to this boy and called him a hero.</i>

02:44.373 --> 02:47.376
<i>Well, I'll tell you what I call him,
public enemy number one!</i>

02:47.459 --> 02:50.712
I told you
I never wanted to do this ever again!

02:51.296 --> 02:54.132
MJ, I'm so sorry, but I can't see anything
with your hand in my--

02:54.216 --> 02:55.759
Sorry. Where are we gonna go?

02:55.843 --> 02:57.636
- I don't know. Your house?
- No!

02:57.719 --> 02:59.012
My dad will kill you.

02:59.096 --> 03:01.139
What? You said your dad really liked me.

03:01.223 --> 03:02.975
Yeah, well, not anymore.

03:05.519 --> 03:06.728
- Dude.
<i>- Dude.</i>

03:06.812 --> 03:07.855
-Dude!
<i>-Dude!</i>

03:07.938 --> 03:08.939
Dude!

03:09.022 --> 03:11.066
<i>-Dude!
</i>-Dude!

03:11.692 --> 03:14.027
I'm so sorry.
Are you okay?

03:14.111 --> 03:16.071
- No, not really. Uh--
- Yo, Peter!

03:24.621 --> 03:26.039
We should go. We should go. Come on.

03:26.123 --> 03:28.458
-You said you don't want to swing.
-You should just swing me.

03:28.542 --> 03:30.043
-Okay. We can take the subway.
-Okay.

03:34.173 --> 03:35.007
No.

03:40.929 --> 03:42.097
Look out!

03:50.898 --> 03:53.442
That was so much worse. Okay. It's okay.

03:53.525 --> 03:56.111
- Are you okay?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

03:56.612 --> 03:58.989
Come on, come on, come on.
Okay, I'm so sorry.

04:09.291 --> 04:10.125
Okay.

04:10.751 --> 04:11.585
Okay.

04:12.252 --> 04:13.420
I'm sorry.

04:15.547 --> 04:18.091
I just feel so dumb.
I didn't realise you were miserable.

04:18.175 --> 04:21.553
No, it was really fun, right?
That's why they call it a fling.

04:21.637 --> 04:25.265
-And we flung.
-It was fun. I could've been more fun.

04:25.349 --> 04:27.768
-We'll hang out again.
-Like, when do you think?

04:30.771 --> 04:33.315
-I should see what that is.
-No, no, no.

04:33.398 --> 04:35.817
- It's what I do. Peter?
- He's always coming and going.

04:35.901 --> 04:37.152
- Peter?
- Oh! Oh, no.

04:37.236 --> 04:38.403
- Oh, God.
- Oh, no.

04:38.487 --> 04:40.113
- I don't know what to do.
- Peter?

04:41.448 --> 04:42.699
-Oh--
-I didn't see anything.

04:42.783 --> 04:44.576
Um, this isn't what it looks like.

04:44.660 --> 04:46.370
-No, no, no, May.
-Practise safe--

04:46.453 --> 04:49.206
Oh, hey. You must be MJ!

04:49.289 --> 04:51.959
- Yeah. Nice to meet you.
- So nice to meet you.

04:52.042 --> 04:54.711
-Wait, have you been crying?
-We broke up.

04:56.505 --> 04:58.757
- Oh. Oh! Uh...
- Hey, Spider-Man!

04:59.675 --> 05:01.301
Thank you. I didn't know you broke up.

05:01.385 --> 05:04.263
I thought you were in love, May.
Can we talk about this in the kitchen?

05:04.346 --> 05:05.973
I should probably leave.

05:06.056 --> 05:08.016
I thought you guys were
such a handsome couple.

05:08.100 --> 05:10.185
It's really about boundaries.

05:10.269 --> 05:12.437
-Let me answer the door.
-Let's go in here.

05:12.521 --> 05:14.022
-Is that the door?
-Hey. Is it true?

05:14.106 --> 05:16.191
- I was gonna go, but...
- Not now.

05:16.275 --> 05:19.236
I didn't know you were
so awkward about sex, Peter.

05:19.319 --> 05:21.405
This has nothing to do with sex.

05:21.488 --> 05:23.991
If you wanna go over it again.
I mean-- What's that sound?

05:24.074 --> 05:24.992
Uh...

05:26.076 --> 05:28.745
- Hey, Spider-Man!
- Oh, my God.

05:28.829 --> 05:31.373
I mean, I'm happy to rehash it
if you want to.

05:31.456 --> 05:34.334
You take care of your side,
I'll take care of mine.

05:34.418 --> 05:37.754
What is up with this phone?

05:37.838 --> 05:40.174
Will you get off your phones
for five minutes?

05:40.257 --> 05:42.551
I just wanna talk to you
about your relationship, okay?

05:42.634 --> 05:43.468
Peter?

05:46.680 --> 05:48.599
What?

05:49.349 --> 05:51.310
- Is that--?
- Is that here?

05:52.019 --> 05:53.020
Um...

06:05.991 --> 06:08.285
- Yo, Peter Parker!
- Yo, Peter!

06:08.368 --> 06:10.329
Maybe it's not such a big deal.

06:10.412 --> 06:11.705
<i>Spider-Menace!</i>

06:12.247 --> 06:14.791
Governments around the world
launch investigations

06:14.875 --> 06:19.004
into the murderer known as Spider-Man,
aka Peter Parker,

06:19.087 --> 06:21.924
aka the web-headed war criminal

06:22.007 --> 06:26.386
who, for years, has been terrorizing
the decent citizens of New York.

06:26.470 --> 06:29.765
<i>Well, now this city and the world see him
for what he truly is.</i>

06:29.848 --> 06:34.394
New details from last week's
devastating attack in London have emerged.

06:34.478 --> 06:37.189
<i>For more, we go now
to Joint Intelligence headquarters.</i>

06:37.272 --> 06:39.942
<i>Authorities,
just a short while ago, confirmed</i>

06:40.025 --> 06:42.277
<i>that the deadly drones used
in the London attack</i>

06:42.361 --> 06:44.655
<i>were designed by Stark Industries.</i>

06:44.738 --> 06:46.740
Federal agents! Open up!

06:46.823 --> 06:48.534
Federal agents? You stay here.

06:49.243 --> 06:50.744
Department of Damage Control.

06:50.827 --> 06:52.746
We have a warrant
for the arrest of Peter Parker.

06:52.829 --> 06:54.623
- You know the Fourth Amendment?
- Sure.

06:54.706 --> 06:57.251
-Unreasonable search and seizure?
-Get in here, guys. Let's go.

06:58.710 --> 07:00.879
I didn't kill Quentin Beck.
The drones did, okay?

07:00.963 --> 07:02.798
-The drones that are yours.
-No.

07:02.881 --> 07:05.175
Nick Fury was there the entire time.

07:05.259 --> 07:06.969
He can explain everything.

07:07.052 --> 07:09.847
Nick Fury has been off-planet
for the last year.

07:09.930 --> 07:11.807
- What?
- Peter! Hey.

07:12.391 --> 07:15.018
MJ! Uh-- They have nothing
to do with this, sir.

07:15.102 --> 07:17.187
Don't say anything
without a lawyer.

07:17.771 --> 07:18.814
I want a lawyer.

07:19.481 --> 07:21.859
-Ms Jones-Watson.
-Jones. I don't go by Watson.

07:22.234 --> 07:26.029
-Ms Jones, why do you want a lawyer if--?
-If I have nothing to hide?

07:26.113 --> 07:27.406
Exactly. Unless--

07:27.489 --> 07:29.283
-I'm actually guilty of something?
-Uh-huh.

07:29.366 --> 07:31.410
I'm very aware of your tactics
and my rights.

07:32.077 --> 07:33.954
Just answer my questions.

07:34.037 --> 07:35.747
I've seen your file.

07:35.831 --> 07:38.959
You're a smart young woman
with a bright future ahead of her.

07:39.501 --> 07:40.586
Why would you risk it all

07:40.669 --> 07:44.047
by getting involved
with a vigilante like Peter Parker?

07:44.131 --> 07:46.091
<i>Washington Monument,</i>

07:46.175 --> 07:48.093
Venice Grand Canal,

07:48.177 --> 07:49.595
Tower Bridge!

07:49.678 --> 07:51.972
You know,
if I didn't know any better, Peter,

07:52.055 --> 07:55.225
it's kind of like
your enemy is national landmarks.

07:58.854 --> 08:01.023
So sorry to keep you waiting.

08:01.106 --> 08:02.649
-Can we get Ned a snack?
-Absolutely.

08:02.733 --> 08:04.026
-He's been waiting.
-I got you.

08:04.109 --> 08:05.736
Dude, I'm so sorry about that.

08:06.403 --> 08:09.114
-I'm not supposed to say anything to you.
-Not even a thing.

08:09.198 --> 08:13.076
I just have one question.
When MJ told you Peter was Spider-Man--

08:13.160 --> 08:14.161
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

08:14.244 --> 08:16.455
-What's up?
-I knew way before MJ did.

08:16.538 --> 08:19.041
-I was Spider-Man's "guy in the chair."
-I know about those.

08:19.124 --> 08:21.376
-Dude, half my guys are guys in the chair.
-Exactly.

08:21.460 --> 08:24.838
You would know.
I literally helped him find the Vulture.

08:24.922 --> 08:27.174
-I didn't know that.
-I helped him hack a suit once

08:27.257 --> 08:28.717
and helped him get to space.

08:28.800 --> 08:32.929
So in Spider-Man's illegal vigilantism,
you were his main accomplice.

08:36.225 --> 08:38.977
I would like to have
my words stricken from the record.

08:39.686 --> 08:44.066
So if you did your job, I wouldn't have
to be on the boat saving people's lives.

08:44.149 --> 08:46.902
I climbed up the side
of the Washington Monument.

08:46.985 --> 08:49.655
Okay, now we're getting to some facts.

08:49.738 --> 08:51.782
Tell me everything you know
about the Night Monkey.

08:51.865 --> 08:53.116
Here's the funny thing about the law.

08:53.200 --> 08:55.869
It's usually not open
to random self-interest interpretation.

08:55.953 --> 08:59.331
Though you and I both know that hasn't
stopped people like you from trying.

08:59.414 --> 09:03.418
So with all due respect,
and I mean that very insincerely,

09:03.502 --> 09:06.588
unless you have
some real specific charges to throw at us,

09:06.672 --> 09:08.215
legally, you can't hold us here.

09:08.298 --> 09:10.843
Sounds like someone
who's been through the system before.

09:10.926 --> 09:14.221
I've been arrested at a couple
of protests. I'm a real career criminal.

09:14.304 --> 09:18.809
You should lawyer up.
Child endangerment's a nasty rap.

09:19.309 --> 09:20.143
Excuse me?

09:20.227 --> 09:21.395
A boy was entrusted to you,

09:21.478 --> 09:23.856
and as his legal guardian,
essentially his mother,

09:23.939 --> 09:28.110
you not only allowed him
to endanger himself, you encouraged it.

09:28.193 --> 09:29.862
Who does that?

09:29.945 --> 09:32.239
I wanna see Peter right now.

09:32.322 --> 09:34.992
<i> Stark Industries
was caught in the web</i>

09:35.075 --> 09:37.744
<i>of the Spider-Man/Mysterio
controversy today,</i>

09:37.828 --> 09:40.330
<i>when federal agents opened
an investigation</i>

09:40.414 --> 09:43.125
<i>into missing Stark technology.</i>

09:43.208 --> 09:45.752
<i>Agents wanna know
exactly what was taken...</i>

09:45.836 --> 09:48.922
-At least they used a good picture.
-What is happening?

09:51.300 --> 09:52.968
That's great.

09:53.051 --> 09:54.052
Thank you.

09:54.136 --> 09:55.846
I have some good news, Peter.

09:55.929 --> 09:58.557
I don't believe any of the charges
against you are gonna stick.

09:58.640 --> 09:59.975
-Wait, seriously?
-Oh.

10:00.058 --> 10:01.018
-I knew it.
-Nice.

10:01.101 --> 10:02.686
Mr Murdock, thank you.

10:02.769 --> 10:04.438
-Thank you.
-That's amazing.

10:04.521 --> 10:06.190
- You're welcome.
- Perfect.

10:06.273 --> 10:07.774
- However, Mr Hogan...
- Yes?

10:07.858 --> 10:11.069
...the feds are investigating
that missing technology.

10:11.153 --> 10:13.488
I understand your loyalty
to Mr Stark and his legacy,

10:13.572 --> 10:14.948
but if you were involved--

10:15.032 --> 10:16.783
-If I was?
-I advise securing a lawyer.

10:16.867 --> 10:19.912
I need a lawyer because I'm--?
I thought he was--

10:19.995 --> 10:23.165
You said there's no charge.
I could say under advisement of counsel,

10:23.248 --> 10:25.292
I refuse to answer
the question respectfully

10:25.375 --> 10:27.336
because the answer can incriminate me--

10:27.419 --> 10:29.922
It's in <i>Goodfellas.
</i>What's the thing they say in <i>Goodfellas?</i>

10:30.005 --> 10:33.258
I know that's what you think. Calm down.
Let's hear what he has to say. Matt?

10:33.342 --> 10:35.177
You're gonna need a really good lawyer.

10:36.094 --> 10:39.681
You may have dodged your legal troubles,
but things will get much worse.

10:39.765 --> 10:41.642
There is still the court
of public opinion.

10:44.353 --> 10:46.647
Murderer! Mysterio forever!

10:49.107 --> 10:50.609
How did you just do that?

10:51.401 --> 10:53.028
I'm a really good lawyer.

10:54.821 --> 10:56.990
We'll need a safer place to live.

11:07.668 --> 11:09.378
Oh. Aah!

11:09.461 --> 11:11.296
How do we--? How do we--?

11:11.380 --> 11:13.882
<i>Alarm system deactivated.</i>

11:16.009 --> 11:18.595
It looks nice. And this is safe.

11:22.015 --> 11:24.726
Welcome to the spiritual oasis.

11:25.394 --> 11:26.895
You like <i>Donkey Kong Jr.?</i>

11:26.979 --> 11:29.773
- Hey, man, move!
- Stop! Thief!

11:29.857 --> 11:31.775
Move out of the way!
Hey, move, move!

11:31.859 --> 11:32.901
Stop that guy!

11:32.985 --> 11:33.902
Look out!

11:33.986 --> 11:35.028
Stop!

11:38.824 --> 11:39.825
Oh, my God.

11:43.704 --> 11:44.830
Hey!

11:44.913 --> 11:47.499
Whoa, what are you doing?
You can't do this anymore.

11:47.583 --> 11:49.042
-He's a thief.
-You're a child.

11:49.126 --> 11:52.754
Show some respect.
He's not a child. He's 14 years old.

11:52.838 --> 11:54.506
-I'm not--
-I had a job when I was 14.

11:54.590 --> 11:57.176
-My son is 14. He's a moron.
-Guys, I am not 14 years old.

11:57.259 --> 11:59.803
He's not equipped
to make these kinds of decisions.

11:59.887 --> 12:02.514
It's true. Teenagers' brains
aren't fully developed yet.

12:02.598 --> 12:04.391
- He can't even rent a car.
- He doesn't need a car.

12:04.474 --> 12:05.976
-He's been to space.
-Thank you.

12:06.059 --> 12:08.687
How do you know they aren't
working together and in cahoots?

12:08.770 --> 12:10.522
Me and this guy? I don't know this guy.

12:10.606 --> 12:12.232
We don't know
what's in that bag.

12:12.316 --> 12:14.318
We've been in cahoots the whole time.

12:14.401 --> 12:15.819
- Murderer!
- Ugh!

12:15.903 --> 12:17.529
Mysterio forever!

12:18.655 --> 12:20.532
Ugh!

12:20.616 --> 12:22.951
<i>Nicky, from Jersey City,
you're on the line.</i>

12:23.035 --> 12:25.662
<i>Hi. I'm not saying
I don't want to honour the Avengers,</i>

12:25.746 --> 12:28.123
<i>but, you know, not doing it this way.</i>

12:28.207 --> 12:31.460
<i>Putting the Captain America shield
on the Statue of Liberty?</i>

12:31.543 --> 12:33.378
<i>Nah, that will look ridiculous.</i>

12:33.462 --> 12:35.506
<i>Leave the Statue of Liberty alone.</i>

12:35.589 --> 12:37.633
Oh, Happy.

12:37.716 --> 12:41.386
- <i>Did you send in your applications?
</i>-I finished my MIT one.

12:41.470 --> 12:42.471
<i>-You?
</i>-Same.

12:42.554 --> 12:44.348
Can you imagine
if we both got in? And Ned?

12:44.431 --> 12:48.310
Yeah, but we'd have to get scholarships
so we could actually go.

12:48.393 --> 12:50.687
You got the scores and the grades.

12:50.771 --> 12:52.231
You think I'm being too pragmatic.

12:52.314 --> 12:53.732
No, no, no. Well...

12:54.983 --> 12:57.569
Kind of. It's okay.
It's one of my favourite things about you.

12:57.653 --> 12:58.946
-Really?
<i>-Yeah.</i>

12:59.029 --> 13:00.864
What are your other favourite things?

13:00.948 --> 13:04.868
-Your relentless optimism.
-I'm a glass-half-full kind of gal.

13:04.952 --> 13:07.579
-I really like how you're a people person.
-I love people.

13:07.663 --> 13:10.123
-I love them so much.
-You like sports.

13:10.207 --> 13:12.376
I think the Mets are gonna go
all the way this year.

13:12.459 --> 13:14.545
-Really?
-What's that noise?

13:14.628 --> 13:15.963
<i>Oh.</i>

13:16.046 --> 13:17.631
<i>It's-- It's Happy. Look.</i>

13:17.714 --> 13:20.551
<i>Gave his room to May,
so he's sleeping down here.</i>

13:24.429 --> 13:26.849
I have a weird question. Um...

13:28.141 --> 13:30.394
Does any part of you
feel relieved about this?

13:33.856 --> 13:36.233
Ever since I got bit by that spider...

13:37.651 --> 13:41.280
I've only had one week
where my life has felt normal.

13:42.030 --> 13:43.824
Or kind of normal, I guess.

13:44.366 --> 13:45.242
And...

13:46.827 --> 13:48.245
that was when you found out.

13:48.328 --> 13:52.958
<i>Because then everyone that was in my life
that I wanted to know knew.</i>

13:53.041 --> 13:54.084
<i>And it was perfect.</i>

13:54.168 --> 13:56.253
But now everybody knows and...

13:58.213 --> 14:01.466
I am the most famous person
in the entire world.

14:02.426 --> 14:04.136
And I'm still broke.

14:08.223 --> 14:09.057
I'm...

14:09.933 --> 14:12.060
excited to see you tomorrow.

14:14.062 --> 14:15.439
Yeah. Me too.

14:15.522 --> 14:16.773
Wrap it up.

14:16.857 --> 14:18.942
You both like each other.
We get it. Hang up.

14:19.026 --> 14:21.528
There's no new ground being broken.
I need my eight hours.

14:21.612 --> 14:23.906
-Have you been listening this whole time?
<i>-Hi, Happy.</i>

14:23.989 --> 14:25.199
Uh, not by choice.

14:25.282 --> 14:27.492
-MJ says hi.
-Hello.

14:27.576 --> 14:29.328
It's back to school, folks.

14:29.411 --> 14:33.248
And in their infinite wisdom,
Mayor Dingus and the city clown-cil

14:33.332 --> 14:36.793
are welcoming back the town's
most notorious costumed killer--

14:36.877 --> 14:38.253
Peter Parker.

14:38.337 --> 14:41.882
Go get them, tiger!
Or should I say "spider"?

14:41.965 --> 14:45.427
<i>The crowd has continued
to grow here all morning long</i>

14:45.511 --> 14:47.513
<i>at the Midtown School of Science...</i>

14:47.596 --> 14:51.558
<i>The crowd seems evenly
divided between supporters of Spider-Man</i>

14:51.642 --> 14:52.643
<i>and protestors.</i>

14:52.726 --> 14:54.436
MJ!

14:54.520 --> 14:56.772
MJ! MJ! We love you!

14:56.855 --> 14:59.274
MJ, are you gonna have his spider-babies?

14:59.358 --> 15:01.443
Back up. Back up. Back up!

15:02.402 --> 15:04.655
MJ, you know he's a murderer, right?

15:04.738 --> 15:06.365
Peter, do a TikTok with me.

15:06.448 --> 15:08.492
Mysterio forever!

15:08.575 --> 15:09.618
Do a flip!

15:09.701 --> 15:12.287
- Hey, let's see you and MJ kiss!
- Back off.

15:12.371 --> 15:13.539
Who are you?

15:13.622 --> 15:16.291
-Ned Leeds. Spider-Man's best friend.
-I'm Peter Parker's best friend.

15:16.375 --> 15:18.961
You come at my boy,
you come at Flash Thompson.

15:19.044 --> 15:21.088
If you wanna read
about our inspiring friendship,

15:21.171 --> 15:23.257
you can in my new book, <i>Flashpoint.</i>

15:23.340 --> 15:26.051
One spider, two hearts,
a million crazy-ass memories.

15:26.134 --> 15:27.386
Check it out.

15:30.097 --> 15:31.598
-Go.
-No, I gotta wait--

15:31.682 --> 15:34.017
- No. Go.
- I'll see you inside, okay?

15:35.769 --> 15:37.896
<i>Keep watching </i>Midtown News <i>all year</i>

15:37.980 --> 15:39.982
<i>as we bring you up-close
and personal coverage</i>

15:40.065 --> 15:43.151
<i>of Peter fighting his biggest battle yet:</i>

15:43.235 --> 15:44.778
<i>College admissions.</i>

15:48.866 --> 15:49.950
Peter,

15:50.033 --> 15:54.413
we would love to welcome you
back to Midtown High,

15:54.496 --> 15:56.123
where we shape heroes.

15:56.206 --> 15:58.083
-Uh-huh.
-Or murderers.

15:58.166 --> 15:59.168
-Stop it.
-Huh?

15:59.251 --> 16:02.921
-It's an honour to serve you, sir.
-It's not.

16:03.005 --> 16:04.339
Mysterio was right.

16:04.423 --> 16:06.133
-Stop. That's all.
-Mysterio was right.

16:06.216 --> 16:08.844
Some students put this together for you.

16:08.927 --> 16:11.722
- No, you did that.
- I helped a little bit.

16:11.805 --> 16:14.725
And I tried to stop you
so many times, but you powered through.

16:14.808 --> 16:16.268
-He did all of that.
-Did a great job.

16:16.351 --> 16:18.770
I hope you have time to check it out.

16:18.854 --> 16:21.565
Feel free to walk
or swing through the hallway.

16:21.648 --> 16:23.901
Or crawl on the ceiling
to avoid everybody.

16:23.984 --> 16:26.403
-We all know you can do it.
-I'm just gonna...

16:26.486 --> 16:28.906
-I know what you did.
-Stop. You're embarrassing yourself.

16:28.989 --> 16:30.616
He's a conspiracy theorist.

16:46.256 --> 16:48.467
We were lab partners. Did you know that?

16:48.550 --> 16:49.384
<i>Climb it!</i>

16:49.468 --> 16:53.889
Climb it! Climb it! Climb it!

17:09.780 --> 17:12.115
Look at that sticky bastard go.

17:12.782 --> 17:13.784
Freak!

17:14.910 --> 17:16.912
I'm where he gets
all his best ideas.

17:16.994 --> 17:18.747
That's why he calls me his Spidey mentor.

17:18.829 --> 17:21.666
Peter! Good to see you, bud!
I'll see you later!

17:23.126 --> 17:25.087
Oh, my God, he's so cute!

17:25.753 --> 17:28.590
<i>What's it like
being Spider-Man's teacher?</i>

17:28.674 --> 17:32.553
<i>Well, Peter's always been
more than a student to me.</i>

17:32.636 --> 17:37.516
He's been more like a son.
Who's also my little brother.

17:37.599 --> 17:39.476
So, what do you think about

17:39.560 --> 17:43.355
these crazy Mysterio conspiracy theories
that are spreading online?

17:43.438 --> 17:45.649
There's a conspiracy theory that

17:45.732 --> 17:48.527
Justin Timberlake was in NSYNC
at one time.

17:48.610 --> 17:51.655
And then you look it up,
and, oh, he was in NSYNC.

17:51.738 --> 17:54.908
My ex-wife, for example,
she's been spending a lot of time online.

17:54.992 --> 17:57.494
And, you know,
the Internet is a wild place

17:57.578 --> 18:01.415
that really beckons people like her
who are a little lost

18:01.498 --> 18:04.418
and kind of have forgotten
where they came from and who they are

18:04.501 --> 18:06.753
and that they love someone very much.

18:07.629 --> 18:10.632
Sometimes you just forget these things
and you end up in a subreddit,

18:11.675 --> 18:13.051
believing in Mysterio.

18:15.012 --> 18:16.388
Sorry, what was your question?

18:16.471 --> 18:19.808
So you never noticed he had
extraordinary athletic abilities?

18:19.892 --> 18:22.477
I mean, it's a science school,

18:23.270 --> 18:26.023
so two push-ups is
extraordinary athletic abilities.

18:26.106 --> 18:30.110
In your book, you revealed
that the name "Spider-Man" was your idea.

18:30.194 --> 18:34.281
Were there any others that you tossed
around before settling on "Spider-Man"?

18:34.364 --> 18:35.991
Yeah, uh, there were a few.

18:36.074 --> 18:38.619
You know, "Arachnokid." "The Bitten."

18:38.702 --> 18:42.539
When I think about it, there were times
that he was sticking to the wall,

18:42.623 --> 18:45.709
or he had this stuff coming out
of his wrist.

18:45.792 --> 18:48.378
But I didn't really
think much of it. I just...

18:49.379 --> 18:53.008
I've been doing this a long time.
It's just a lot of kids.

18:53.091 --> 18:56.845
I noticed that in your book
I'm not mentioned once.

18:56.929 --> 19:00.390
No. No, I'm pretty sure you are. Uh...

19:01.225 --> 19:02.476
I mean, you're...

19:02.559 --> 19:04.436
Whoa, there are pictures in this?

19:04.520 --> 19:06.480
If that spider had bitten me,

19:07.481 --> 19:09.149
we'd be talking about
a different Spider-Man right now.

19:09.233 --> 19:13.111
I think I would have maybe had
a different style costume.

19:13.195 --> 19:15.489
Maybe something with flared legs, maybe.

19:15.572 --> 19:16.532
As sexy as possible.

19:16.615 --> 19:19.326
So, what is an appropriate text to send

19:19.409 --> 19:21.537
to an ex-girlfriend
in the middle of the night?

19:26.708 --> 19:28.001
You look great, by the way.

19:28.085 --> 19:31.839
Thank you. You look as beautiful as ever.

19:32.589 --> 19:34.716
What do you say
to the people who claim

19:34.800 --> 19:37.719
that you're not really friends
with Peter Parker?

19:42.516 --> 19:43.851
You know, it hurts.

19:43.934 --> 19:44.935
Because...

19:46.895 --> 19:48.355
You know, I...

19:48.438 --> 19:49.523
Tell me:

19:49.606 --> 19:53.485
If the spider that gave you
your powers were here right now,

19:54.236 --> 19:55.445
what would you say?

19:56.029 --> 19:59.825
Would you say, "Thanks"?
Or, "Thanks for nothing"?

19:59.908 --> 20:01.743
I would say "Thanks."

20:02.953 --> 20:03.829
"For nothing"?

20:03.912 --> 20:06.039
You can catch the rest
of my exclusive interview

20:06.123 --> 20:09.710
with Peter Parker today at lunch,
only on MNN.

20:09.793 --> 20:13.338
<i>Up next, Lady Liberty is getting
a makeover,</i>

20:13.422 --> 20:15.674
<i>and some of Midtown High's
very own artists share</i>

20:15.757 --> 20:18.260
<i>their ideas of what she should look like.</i>

20:18.343 --> 20:20.721
We'll be right back
after this important message

20:20.804 --> 20:23.473
from Principal Morita
about cafeteria safety.

20:27.311 --> 20:29.396
Can we just stay up here all day?

20:29.479 --> 20:32.191
- It is so crazy down there.
- This one's good.

20:32.274 --> 20:35.360
"Some suggest that Parker's powers
include the male spider's ability

20:35.444 --> 20:37.070
to hypnotise females,

20:37.154 --> 20:41.533
which he used to seduce Jones-Watson
into his cult of personality."

20:41.617 --> 20:43.327
Stop. Stop.

20:43.410 --> 20:44.995
Yes, my Spider-Lord.

20:52.961 --> 20:55.214
Finally, some privacy.

20:55.297 --> 20:57.007
It is so crazy down there.

20:57.883 --> 20:59.468
So I was thinking...

21:00.135 --> 21:03.472
when we get into MIT,
we should live together.

21:03.555 --> 21:05.516
- Yeah, for sure.
- Yeah, I'd love that.

21:07.476 --> 21:11.021
-This is gonna be us.
-Yes. Minus the Frisbee and the smiling.

21:11.104 --> 21:12.856
MIT's obviously the dream,

21:12.940 --> 21:17.319
but if we match up our backup schools,
then either way, we'll be in Boston.

21:17.402 --> 21:19.404
New school, new town.
I can Spider-Man there.

21:19.488 --> 21:21.657
-They have crime in Boston, right?
-Yes.

21:21.740 --> 21:24.368
- Wicked crime.
- It'll be like a fresh start.

21:26.078 --> 21:27.329
What's up?

21:28.121 --> 21:30.040
I don't know.
I just feel like, if you don't--

21:30.749 --> 21:32.626
If you expect disappointment,

21:32.709 --> 21:35.212
then you can never really
get disappointed.

21:35.295 --> 21:36.421
Come on.

21:37.589 --> 21:40.801
Be a fresh start.
And we'll all be together.

21:42.386 --> 21:44.680
Yeah. No, you're right. Fresh start.

21:44.763 --> 21:45.597
Yeah.

21:48.559 --> 21:49.643
Fresh start.

21:52.312 --> 21:53.564
First one's here!

21:58.151 --> 21:59.903
It's okay. It's a backup.

22:01.280 --> 22:02.197
Peter.

22:04.533 --> 22:05.367
No?

22:08.161 --> 22:09.037
Last one.

22:10.914 --> 22:11.874
MIT?!

22:15.919 --> 22:17.462
Uh-- Okay.

22:29.057 --> 22:31.226
-Okay.
-Whew.

22:31.310 --> 22:32.728
- Ready?
- Jones,

22:32.811 --> 22:35.439
I told you to take down
the Halloween decorations.

22:35.522 --> 22:38.859
- Actually, that was Sasha, so--
- Enough attitude. Just do it.

22:40.068 --> 22:40.903
On it.

22:42.196 --> 22:43.739
Feel like I'm gonna puke.

22:43.822 --> 22:46.450
Don't, because he will
just make me clean it.

22:46.533 --> 22:49.119
This is our only shot.
It's here or nowhere.

22:49.203 --> 22:51.288
-Hey. Come on.
-Okay. You ready?

22:51.371 --> 22:53.332
- Yeah.
- Okay, on three.

22:53.999 --> 22:56.793
One, two, three.

23:20.234 --> 23:21.318
No.

23:21.401 --> 23:23.445
No. You?

23:24.530 --> 23:26.615
"In light of recent controversy,

23:26.698 --> 23:31.286
we are unable to consider
your application at this time."

23:31.912 --> 23:33.121
This is so not fair.

23:33.622 --> 23:36.166
I mean, this is so not fair.
I didn't do anything wrong.

23:36.250 --> 23:38.335
You guys definitely didn't do
anything wrong.

23:38.418 --> 23:41.964
Expect disappointment
and you will never get disappointed.

23:43.590 --> 23:45.384
<i>♪ No sleep till ♪</i>

23:45.467 --> 23:48.595
<i>♪ Bom, bom, tsk, bom, bom ♪</i>

23:48.679 --> 23:49.930
<i>♪ Boston! ♪</i>

23:55.352 --> 23:56.270
You didn't get in?

23:56.353 --> 23:58.856
Yeah, because we're actually friends
with Spider-Man.

24:01.233 --> 24:03.402
Uh, yeah. I better get going.

24:03.485 --> 24:06.530
There's a mixer for new admissions and--

24:06.613 --> 24:08.031
Sorry, guys.

24:08.615 --> 24:10.534
Jones, what are you doing?
Get back to work.

24:10.617 --> 24:12.077
Yeah, I'm coming.

24:12.160 --> 24:13.078
Know what?

24:14.997 --> 24:16.623
I wouldn't change a thing I did.

24:18.000 --> 24:18.876
Me neither.

24:22.546 --> 24:25.007
Although I do need
to show this letter to my parents.

25:35.452 --> 25:36.662
Um, hi.

25:39.873 --> 25:40.707
Hi?

25:41.959 --> 25:42.793
I'm, uh--

25:43.544 --> 25:46.463
The most famous person
in the world. I know.

25:47.798 --> 25:51.677
Wong. Try not to slip.
We don't have liability insurance.

25:54.972 --> 25:57.391
-Is all this for a holiday party?
-No.

25:57.474 --> 26:00.561
One of the rotunda gateways
connects to Siberia.

26:00.644 --> 26:03.021
A blizzard blasted through.

26:04.356 --> 26:07.025
Because someone forgot
to cast a monthly maintenance spell

26:07.109 --> 26:08.443
to keep the seals tight.

26:08.527 --> 26:11.738
That's right, he did, because he forgot
I now have higher duties.

26:11.822 --> 26:12.948
Higher duties?

26:13.031 --> 26:15.242
The Sorcerer Supreme has higher duties.

26:15.325 --> 26:17.494
Wait, I thought
you were the Sorcerer Supreme.

26:17.578 --> 26:21.081
No, he got it on a technicality
'cause I blipped for five years.

26:21.164 --> 26:23.876
-Oh. Congratulations.
-If I'd been here, then--

26:23.959 --> 26:25.169
You'd burn the place down.

26:25.252 --> 26:27.588
You two, no one said stop shovelling.

26:27.671 --> 26:30.257
So, Peter, to what do I owe the pleasure?

26:30.883 --> 26:34.011
Right. Um, I'm really sorry
to bother you, sir.

26:34.094 --> 26:36.054
Please. We saved half
the universe together.

26:36.138 --> 26:39.766
-Think we're beyond you calling me "sir."
-Okay, uh, Stephen.

26:39.850 --> 26:41.435
That feels weird, but I'll allow it.

26:42.394 --> 26:43.353
Uh...

26:44.313 --> 26:45.147
When, um...

26:46.064 --> 26:48.192
When Mysterio revealed my identity,

26:49.151 --> 26:52.905
my entire life got screwed up,
and I was wondering--

26:52.988 --> 26:55.908
I don't know if this would actually work,
but I was wondering if...

26:57.868 --> 27:00.913
maybe you could go back in time
and make it so he never did?

27:02.581 --> 27:06.376
Peter, we tampered
with the stability of space-time

27:06.460 --> 27:08.253
to resurrect countless lives.

27:08.337 --> 27:10.589
You wanna do it again now
just 'cause yours got messy?

27:10.672 --> 27:12.049
It's not about me.

27:12.132 --> 27:14.218
This is really hurting a lot of people.

27:14.301 --> 27:17.304
My aunt May, Happy,

27:17.387 --> 27:18.805
my best friend, my girlfriend,

27:18.889 --> 27:20.849
their futures are ruined
just because they know me,

27:20.933 --> 27:22.976
and they've done nothing wrong.

27:23.060 --> 27:25.062
I am so sorry...

27:26.146 --> 27:27.481
but even if I wanted to...

27:28.357 --> 27:30.734
I don't have the Time Stone anymore.

27:33.070 --> 27:34.071
That's right.

27:37.824 --> 27:41.411
I'm really sorry if I wasted your time.

27:41.495 --> 27:43.539
- You didn't.
- Just forget about it.

27:43.622 --> 27:46.458
Oh, he will.
He's very good at forgetting things.

27:48.043 --> 27:50.963
Wong, you've actually generated
a good idea.

27:51.046 --> 27:52.047
What?

27:52.130 --> 27:54.216
The Runes of Kof-Kol.

27:54.299 --> 27:55.884
The Runes of Kof-Kol?

27:55.968 --> 27:58.303
It's just a standard spell of forgetting.

27:58.387 --> 28:01.348
Won't turn back time, but people will
forget you were ever Spider-Man.

28:01.431 --> 28:03.350
-Seriously?
-No, not seriously.

28:03.433 --> 28:07.020
That spell travels the dark borders
between known and unknown reality.

28:07.104 --> 28:08.313
It's too dangerous.

28:09.314 --> 28:11.024
We've used it for a lot less.

28:11.108 --> 28:13.235
Do you remember
the full-moon party at Kamar-Taj?

28:13.318 --> 28:14.862
-No.
-Exactly.

28:18.323 --> 28:19.867
Come on, Wong.

28:21.368 --> 28:23.161
Hasn't he been through enough?

28:30.294 --> 28:31.837
Just leave me out of this.

28:32.713 --> 28:33.547
Fine.

28:34.965 --> 28:35.799
Fine.

28:48.020 --> 28:49.396
So, what is this place?

28:50.397 --> 28:54.276
The Sanctum's built at the intersection
of cosmic energy currents.

28:54.359 --> 28:55.986
We weren't the first to seek them out.

28:56.695 --> 28:59.114
Some of these walls
are thousands of years old.

29:00.073 --> 29:03.744
And they shot an episode
of <i>The Equalizer</i> here in the '80s.

29:03.827 --> 29:04.912
Well, I, um...

29:06.747 --> 29:08.582
really appreciate you
doing this for me, sir.

29:09.374 --> 29:10.501
Don't mention it.

29:12.252 --> 29:13.879
And don't call me "sir."

29:15.005 --> 29:15.881
Right. Sorry.

29:16.715 --> 29:17.883
You ready?

29:18.926 --> 29:19.760
I'm ready.

29:22.012 --> 29:23.472
Nice knowing you, Spider-Man.

29:28.185 --> 29:29.102
Wait, excuse me?

29:31.188 --> 29:34.566
The entire world's about to forget
that Peter Parker is Spider-Man.

29:35.192 --> 29:36.777
-Including me.
-Everyone?

29:37.611 --> 29:41.240
-Uh, can't some people still know?
-That's not how the spell works.

29:41.323 --> 29:45.202
And it's very difficult and dangerous
to change it mid-casting.

29:45.285 --> 29:47.412
So my girlfriend's gonna
forget everything?

29:47.496 --> 29:48.997
Is she even gonna be my girlfriend?

29:49.081 --> 29:51.458
Was she your girlfriend
just 'cause you were Spider-Man?

29:51.542 --> 29:54.002
-I don't know. I really hope not.
-All right, fine.

29:55.504 --> 29:59.550
Everyone's gonna forget
you're Spider-Man except your girlfriend.

29:59.633 --> 30:00.759
Thank you so much.

30:01.510 --> 30:03.387
Oh, my God, Ned. Ned.

30:04.930 --> 30:06.390
What is a Ned?

30:06.473 --> 30:09.309
He's my best friend,
so it's important to me that Ned knows.

30:13.647 --> 30:18.193
Okay, let's not change
the parameters of this spell any more

30:18.277 --> 30:20.070
-while I'm casting it.
-Okay, I'm done.

30:20.153 --> 30:21.363
I swear, I'm done. I'm done.

30:21.864 --> 30:25.117
-Ah, but my aunt May should really know.
-Peter, stop tampering with the spell.

30:25.200 --> 30:27.619
When she found out I was Spider-Man,
it was really messy.

30:27.703 --> 30:29.913
I don't think
I could go through that again.

30:31.206 --> 30:32.332
-So my aunt May?
-Yes.

30:32.416 --> 30:33.959
Oh. Thank you. Happy?

30:34.042 --> 30:35.252
No, I'm annoyed.

30:35.335 --> 30:37.296
No, it's a nickname. Harold "Happy" Hogan.

30:37.379 --> 30:39.506
He used to work with Tony Stark,
but then he was...

30:39.590 --> 30:41.258
Would you just stop talking?

30:49.349 --> 30:53.687
Basically, everyone that knew
I was Spider-Man before should still know!

31:14.249 --> 31:15.459
-Did it work?
-No.

31:15.542 --> 31:18.629
You changed my spell six times.

31:18.712 --> 31:20.339
-Five times.
-You changed my spell.

31:20.422 --> 31:23.759
You don't do that! I told you.
And that is why.

31:23.842 --> 31:26.512
That spell was out of control.
If I hadn't shut it down,

31:26.595 --> 31:28.931
something catastrophic
could have happened.

31:29.014 --> 31:31.642
-Stephen, listen, I am so--
-Call me "sir."

31:34.186 --> 31:35.395
Sorry, sir.

31:36.313 --> 31:38.524
After everything
we've been through,

31:38.607 --> 31:41.818
somehow I always forget you're just a kid.

31:42.819 --> 31:45.906
Look, Parker, the problem is not Mysterio.

31:45.989 --> 31:48.242
It's you trying
to live two different lives.

31:48.325 --> 31:50.786
And the longer you do that,
the more dangerous it becomes.

31:50.869 --> 31:52.079
Believe me.

31:52.162 --> 31:55.999
I'm so sorry about you
and your friends not getting into college,

31:56.083 --> 32:00.712
but if they rejected you and you tried
to convince them to reconsider,

32:00.796 --> 32:02.965
there's nothing else you can do.

32:06.134 --> 32:08.053
When you say "convince them,"

32:08.136 --> 32:10.764
-you mean, I could have called them?
-Yeah.

32:11.265 --> 32:12.391
I could do that?

32:13.976 --> 32:15.811
You haven't called the...?

32:15.894 --> 32:17.646
I got their letter. I assumed that was--

32:17.729 --> 32:18.856
I'm sorry.

32:19.398 --> 32:20.691
Are you telling me

32:21.233 --> 32:24.027
that you didn't even think
to plead your case with them first

32:24.111 --> 32:27.865
before you asked me
to brainwash the entire world?

32:30.826 --> 32:32.536
When you put it like that...

32:40.377 --> 32:41.962
Come on, pick up, pick up.

32:42.045 --> 32:43.422
Dude, what? I'm busy.

32:43.505 --> 32:45.090
Flash, where's the MIT mixer?

32:45.174 --> 32:47.009
<i>-Why?
</i>-Because I need to talk to someone.

32:47.092 --> 32:49.344
I'm trying to get Ned and MJ
a second chance at getting in.

32:49.428 --> 32:50.637
What's in it for me?

32:50.721 --> 32:52.431
<i>I'm risking a lot just talking to you.</i>

32:52.514 --> 32:54.558
Okay, I will, um...

32:55.934 --> 32:58.228
pick you up and swing you
to school for one week?

32:58.312 --> 32:59.146
For a month.

32:59.688 --> 33:01.440
<i>-For a week.
</i>-Two weeks.

33:01.523 --> 33:03.775
-Flash, please. Help me.
-You know what I want.

33:05.903 --> 33:07.863
Okay, I'll tell everyone
you're my best friend.

33:07.946 --> 33:09.907
<i>-Flash, please, help me.
</i>-Cool.

33:09.990 --> 33:12.993
<i>There's the assistant vice chancellor.
You can plead your case with her.</i>

33:13.076 --> 33:14.786
-Okay, perfect. Where is she?
-She left.

33:14.870 --> 33:16.622
-To go where?
-To the airport.

33:23.295 --> 33:25.756
- <i>Stark network unavailable.</i>

33:25.839 --> 33:28.300
<i>Facial recognition unavailable.</i>

33:31.553 --> 33:32.554
Hi.

33:34.515 --> 33:36.391
Yeah, I can see you.

33:46.068 --> 33:47.611
Oh, my God!

33:49.947 --> 33:51.573
- That's Peter Parker.
- Mom.

33:51.657 --> 33:53.242
- Mom, look.
- Mommy.

33:53.325 --> 33:54.910
No, it's Peter Parker.

34:04.586 --> 34:05.420
Hey!

34:06.171 --> 34:07.005
Okay.

34:18.016 --> 34:19.016
Yeah.

34:19.685 --> 34:20.978
Hi. I'm Peter Parker.

34:21.061 --> 34:23.605
-You do know you're in the street, right?
-Yeah, I'm sorry.

34:23.688 --> 34:26.859
I really needed to talk to you and I know
you're on your way to the airport.

34:26.942 --> 34:30.487
MJ Watson and Ned Leeds are
the two smartest people I've ever met,

34:30.571 --> 34:32.947
and I'm the dumbest person
because I let them help me,

34:33.031 --> 34:34.949
but if I didn't, millions would've died,

34:35.033 --> 34:37.159
so please don't let MIT be dumb like me.

34:37.244 --> 34:38.245
MIT is dumb?

34:38.328 --> 34:41.248
No, I'm saying, don't let MIT be dumb.

34:41.331 --> 34:45.878
I mean, like the dumber version of me
that wouldn't have let them help.

34:47.588 --> 34:50.757
You didn't rehearse that, did you, Peter?

34:50.841 --> 34:52.426
Basically, what I'm trying to--

35:00.517 --> 35:01.727
Why are you running?

35:05.814 --> 35:06.815
Oh, my God.

35:07.316 --> 35:09.443
Uh, ma'am, you should get out of the car.

35:09.526 --> 35:11.695
Everybody get off the bridge!

35:13.614 --> 35:14.698
The door's locked.

35:14.781 --> 35:16.450
Door's-- Hey!

35:33.425 --> 35:34.635
Hello, Peter.

35:35.677 --> 35:37.679
Hi? Do we--? Do I know you?

35:37.763 --> 35:40.015
What have you done with my machine?

35:40.098 --> 35:42.935
I don't know what you're talking about.
What machine?

35:43.018 --> 35:45.854
The power of the sun
in the palm of my hand.

35:46.438 --> 35:47.356
It's gone.

35:47.439 --> 35:49.525
Listen, if you stop smashing cars,

35:49.608 --> 35:52.236
we can work together
and I can help you find your machine.

35:52.319 --> 35:53.820
You want to play games?

35:56.490 --> 35:57.783
Catch!

36:14.675 --> 36:17.094
It's okay.
You're safe. Get out of here.

36:17.177 --> 36:19.888
You think
your fancy new suit's gonna save you?

36:34.778 --> 36:37.739
Should've killed your little girlfriend
when I had the chance.

36:41.702 --> 36:43.120
What did you just say?

36:43.203 --> 36:45.372
Looks like we got competition.

37:05.309 --> 37:07.060
Peter! Help!

37:29.499 --> 37:31.919
Don't worry, ma'am!
I'm coming!

37:33.754 --> 37:35.839
Peter!

38:01.865 --> 38:03.408
Ma'am, just stay calm.

38:03.492 --> 38:04.660
Just take a deep breath.

38:04.743 --> 38:06.411
-Are you okay?
-No!

38:08.789 --> 38:11.333
I promise,
I've got this all under control.

38:17.339 --> 38:19.716
- Whoa!
<i>- Suit compromised.</i>

38:20.342 --> 38:21.802
Nanotechnology.

38:22.553 --> 38:24.805
Ah, you've outdone yourself, Peter.

38:31.103 --> 38:32.688
I underestimated you.

38:34.022 --> 38:35.357
But now you die.

38:51.790 --> 38:53.208
You're not Peter Parker.

38:53.292 --> 38:55.669
I am so confused right now.

38:58.422 --> 38:59.506
What's happening?

38:59.590 --> 39:01.133
<i>New device detected.</i>

39:03.260 --> 39:04.428
<i>Pairing new device.</i>

39:08.307 --> 39:11.185
You don't listen to him. You listen to me.

39:17.065 --> 39:17.941
Hey.

39:25.866 --> 39:27.534
Whoa!

39:31.079 --> 39:32.789
Hey. Hey!

39:32.873 --> 39:33.999
Listen to me.

39:34.791 --> 39:36.710
No, not him. Me!

39:43.592 --> 39:44.885
Ma'am, you okay?

39:44.968 --> 39:48.472
- You can still make your flight.
- Peter.

39:50.182 --> 39:51.266
You're a hero.

39:51.350 --> 39:52.601
No. Well, I'm--

39:52.684 --> 39:53.769
No, I'm--

39:53.852 --> 39:56.605
I'm gonna talk to Admissions
about your friends.

39:56.688 --> 39:58.148
And I'm gonna talk to them about you.

39:59.233 --> 40:01.401
But, ma'am, this isn't about me.

40:01.485 --> 40:05.447
I am going to talk to them
about your friends and you.

40:05.531 --> 40:07.115
-Okay?
-Really?

40:07.199 --> 40:10.202
And if you keep your noses clean,
maybe you'll have a fair shot.

40:10.285 --> 40:12.120
Here. Get out of the way.
Let me get that man.

40:12.204 --> 40:14.873
Hey. You. I see you. Come here!

40:14.957 --> 40:16.250
That was not okay.

40:16.333 --> 40:17.417
Unbelievable.

40:18.836 --> 40:20.087
Who are--?

40:20.170 --> 40:21.338
Hey. Hey, hey, hey.

40:21.421 --> 40:24.299
Until you stop trying to kill me,
I'm in control, buddy,

40:24.383 --> 40:28.053
of this whole tentacle situation
you got going on here, okay?

40:28.136 --> 40:30.138
Now, who are you? What is going--?

40:39.523 --> 40:40.399
No.

40:47.447 --> 40:48.657
Osborn?

41:11.555 --> 41:14.016
Doctor--?

41:20.272 --> 41:24.484
Be careful what you wish for, Parker.

41:24.568 --> 41:26.111
Let me out of here!

41:26.195 --> 41:28.238
Can you please explain to me
what is going on?

41:28.322 --> 41:29.948
That little spell that you botched

41:30.032 --> 41:32.826
where you wanted everyone
to forget that Peter Parker's Spider-Man,

41:32.910 --> 41:35.829
it started pulling in everyone
who knows Peter Parker's Spider-Man

41:35.913 --> 41:38.582
from every universe into this one.

41:39.666 --> 41:42.628
-From every universe?
-Who are you? And where am I?

41:42.711 --> 41:45.214
I think it's better we don't engage
with them because, frankly,

41:45.297 --> 41:49.426
the multiverse is a concept
about which we know frighteningly little.

41:50.052 --> 41:51.512
The multiverse is real?

41:51.595 --> 41:54.014
This shouldn't be possible.

41:54.097 --> 41:56.350
-I thought you stopped the spell.
-No, I contained it.

41:56.433 --> 41:58.685
It would appear
a few of them squeaked through.

41:58.769 --> 42:01.063
After you left,
I detected an otherworldly presence.

42:01.146 --> 42:03.899
I pursued it into the sewers,
where I found that...

42:04.566 --> 42:06.985
slimy, green son of a gun.

42:07.069 --> 42:09.363
Spell? As in magic?

42:09.947 --> 42:11.865
What is this, a birthday party?

42:11.949 --> 42:14.451
Who is this clown? What is this madness?

42:14.535 --> 42:17.913
Watch this. Do you know
a Peter Parker who's Spider-Man?

42:17.996 --> 42:19.456
-Yes.
-Is that him?

42:19.540 --> 42:21.041
-No.
-See?

42:22.626 --> 42:24.169
Here's what we gotta do.

42:24.253 --> 42:26.588
I don't know how many visitors we've got--

42:26.672 --> 42:29.216
I saw another one on the bridge.

42:29.299 --> 42:32.761
He was like a flying green elf.

42:32.845 --> 42:34.847
He sounds jolly. Start with him.

42:34.930 --> 42:37.599
I need you to capture them,
bring them here while I figure out

42:37.683 --> 42:41.353
how to get them back
before they destroy the fabric of reality,

42:41.436 --> 42:43.230
or worse, Wong finds out.

42:43.814 --> 42:45.399
Uh, Doctor Strange?

42:45.482 --> 42:46.316
What?

42:46.817 --> 42:50.195
My friends and I just got
a second chance to get into MIT,

42:50.279 --> 42:53.073
and if the school sees me
fighting these crazy monsters--

42:53.156 --> 42:54.867
-Hey, watch your mouth.
-I'm sorry, but--

42:54.950 --> 42:57.160
Are you seriously
still talking about college?

42:57.244 --> 42:58.787
Whoa--

43:02.916 --> 43:05.210
-Hey, what did you just do?
-This.

43:06.879 --> 43:08.922
Hey, you can't just-- Oh!

43:11.175 --> 43:14.094
-How did you do that?
-Lots of birthday parties.

43:18.140 --> 43:19.141
Whoa!

43:20.475 --> 43:21.768
Hey.

43:23.937 --> 43:24.813
Whoa.

43:24.897 --> 43:27.107
One shot, send them here, move on.
You're welcome.

43:27.191 --> 43:28.817
-Get to work.
-Sir?

43:29.359 --> 43:30.694
Now what?

43:31.820 --> 43:34.531
This is my mess,
and I swear that I'll fix it,

43:34.615 --> 43:36.158
but I'm gonna need help.

43:37.492 --> 43:38.452
Whoa.

43:39.077 --> 43:41.788
I can't believe
I'm in the Sanctum Sanctorum.

43:41.872 --> 43:43.081
Neither can I.

43:43.749 --> 43:46.293
So how did you know
you were a man of magic?

43:46.376 --> 43:48.545
Because my nana says
that we have it in our family,

43:48.629 --> 43:51.673
-and I get these tinglings in my hands--
-Talk to your physician.

43:51.757 --> 43:53.091
- Peter.
- Hey.

43:53.175 --> 43:54.968
- Hey. Hey.
- Hey. Hey.

43:55.052 --> 43:56.595
Sorry for dragging you into this.

43:56.678 --> 43:59.473
-Help me find these guys.
-You don't have to apologise, okay?

43:59.556 --> 44:01.642
You got us
a second shot at MIT. It's fine.

44:01.725 --> 44:04.311
So how did the bad guys get here?

44:04.394 --> 44:07.523
We screwed up a spell
trying to get you into college.

44:07.606 --> 44:10.359
-You did it with magic?
-I thought it was the MIT lady you saved.

44:10.442 --> 44:13.695
Uh, no, that was after.
Let's just focus on the good news, okay?

44:13.779 --> 44:15.489
No, let's just focus on the bad news.

44:15.572 --> 44:19.660
As of now, you have detected
zero multiversal trespassers,

44:19.743 --> 44:23.997
so get on your phones,
scour the Internet, and...

44:24.081 --> 44:25.415
Scooby-Doo this shit.

44:26.416 --> 44:30.379
You're telling us what to do, even though
it was your spell that got screwed up,

44:30.462 --> 44:32.548
meaning that all this is your mess.

44:32.631 --> 44:37.386
I know a couple of magic words myself,
starting with the word "please."

44:40.264 --> 44:42.808
Please Scooby-Doo this shit.

44:43.517 --> 44:45.394
You can work in the undercroft.

44:45.936 --> 44:48.272
The undercroft?

44:53.151 --> 44:54.194
Badass.

44:57.364 --> 44:58.240
Oh...

45:00.951 --> 45:03.912
-About this whole spell thing--
-It's totally okay.

45:03.996 --> 45:06.582
-Really?
-Yeah. I mean, I get it.

45:06.665 --> 45:10.878
You were just trying
to fix things, and so...

45:10.961 --> 45:13.672
Maybe just run it by us next time,
you know?

45:13.755 --> 45:16.216
That way, when you're thinking,
"I'm about to do something

45:16.300 --> 45:18.969
that could break the universe,"

45:19.052 --> 45:22.306
we could, like, help you
workshop something or...

45:22.931 --> 45:25.559
brainstorm ideas.

45:27.686 --> 45:28.520
Deal.

45:30.105 --> 45:31.148
Ned?

45:31.899 --> 45:35.777
Oh, dude, I don't care.
It's seriously not a big deal. Um--

45:35.861 --> 45:37.112
Oh!

45:37.196 --> 45:39.323
A torture rack.

45:41.116 --> 45:42.701
That is a Pilates machine.

45:43.493 --> 45:44.828
-That is--
-The crypt.

45:44.912 --> 45:47.080
Okay, so we get the rest of the guys,

45:47.164 --> 45:49.166
you zap them,
Doctor Magic will send them back,

45:49.249 --> 45:53.253
and when we get into MIT,
round of stale doughnuts, my treat.

45:53.337 --> 45:55.047
Let's catch some multiverse men.

45:55.130 --> 45:58.091
Hey! Who the hell are these two?

45:58.175 --> 46:00.719
-My friends. This is MJ. And this is Ned.
-Hey.

46:00.802 --> 46:01.637
Hello.

46:02.179 --> 46:05.599
-Uh, sorry, what was your name again?
-Dr Otto Octavius.

46:10.604 --> 46:12.314
Seriously, what's your actual name?

46:12.397 --> 46:13.899
Oh, is that a dinosaur?

46:16.485 --> 46:23.408
<i>♪ I was working in the lab, late one night
When my eyes beheld an eerie sight ♪</i>

46:23.492 --> 46:26.828
<i>♪ For my monster from his slab
Began to rise ♪</i>

46:26.912 --> 46:30.082
<i>♪ And suddenly to my surprise ♪</i>

46:30.165 --> 46:33.502
<i>-♪ He did the mash ♪
-♪ He did the monster mash ♪</i>

46:33.585 --> 46:37.256
<i>-♪ The monster mash ♪
-♪ It was a graveyard smash ♪</i>

46:37.339 --> 46:40.384
<i>-♪ He did the mash ♪
-♪ It caught on in a flash ♪</i>

46:40.467 --> 46:43.887
<i>-♪ He did the mash ♪
-♪ He did the monster mash ♪</i>

46:43.971 --> 46:47.349
<i>♪ From my laboratory in the castle east ♪</i>

46:47.432 --> 46:51.061
<i>♪ To the master bedroom
Where the vampires feast ♪</i>

46:51.144 --> 46:54.606
<i>♪ The ghouls all came
From their humble abodes ♪</i>

46:54.690 --> 46:57.943
<i>♪ To get a jolt from my electrodes ♪</i>

46:58.026 --> 47:01.154
<i>-♪ They did the mash ♪
-♪ They did the monster mash ♪</i>

47:01.238 --> 47:04.074
<i>-♪ The monster mash ♪
-♪ It was a graveyard smash ♪♪</i>

47:04.616 --> 47:05.450
What?

47:08.328 --> 47:09.913
What are you looking at?

47:11.707 --> 47:14.126
<i> If the paint
won't come off, I'll get it out.</i>

47:14.209 --> 47:16.920
No, no, no, May.
We gotta find these guys first.

47:17.004 --> 47:19.089
<i>Finish your mission and then come by.</i>

47:19.173 --> 47:20.632
<i>We're having a canned-food drive.</i>

47:21.341 --> 47:23.468
- That could work.
- I got one!

47:23.552 --> 47:24.845
-I gotta go.
<i>-Okay.</i>

47:24.928 --> 47:27.014
I mean, you can take
the guy out of the chair,

47:27.097 --> 47:29.266
but you can't take
the chair out of the guy.

47:29.349 --> 47:31.685
-What'd you find?
-There's a...

47:31.768 --> 47:35.439
A disturbance near a military
research facility outside of the city,

47:35.522 --> 47:39.318
and witnesses say that they saw
a monster flying through the air.

47:40.694 --> 47:42.779
It's gotta be the guy
I saw on the bridge.

47:42.863 --> 47:44.156
That's impossible.

47:46.742 --> 47:47.951
You know him, don't you?

47:49.119 --> 47:51.121
On the bridge, you said his name.

47:52.456 --> 47:53.790
Norman Osborn.

47:54.666 --> 47:57.920
Brilliant scientist. Military research.

47:59.171 --> 48:01.924
But he was greedy, misguided.

48:02.633 --> 48:06.261
- What happened to him?
- We tire of your questions, boy!

48:07.596 --> 48:08.847
Okay. Um...

48:09.806 --> 48:13.143
-I gotta go. Where am I going?
-It can't be him.

48:15.229 --> 48:16.396
Why?

48:16.480 --> 48:19.942
Because Norman Osborn died years ago.

48:21.193 --> 48:23.362
So either we saw someone else...

48:24.947 --> 48:29.826
or you're flying out
into the darkness to fight a ghost.

48:53.267 --> 48:56.019
Keep an eye out on the trees.
We don't know where this guy is.

48:59.189 --> 49:01.900
I genuinely don't know
how you do this without throwing up.

49:19.960 --> 49:22.588
- Did you see that?
<i>- Um...</i>

49:22.671 --> 49:24.673
<i>- No.
- </i>-<i>It's really dark.</i>

49:37.144 --> 49:38.854
Okay, okay, okay.

49:45.736 --> 49:46.945
<i>What's happening?</i>

49:47.029 --> 49:48.197
<i>Peter, what is it?</i>

49:50.574 --> 49:52.117
<i>Are you getting the tingle thing?</i>

49:52.201 --> 49:54.620
<i>Is the tingle happening?
Is your tingle tingling?</i>

50:03.712 --> 50:05.631
- Are you guys seeing this?
<i>- Yeah.</i>

50:06.381 --> 50:08.759
- <i>Osborn?
</i>-No. He was green. This guy's blue.

50:09.593 --> 50:13.639
Uh, you wouldn't happen
to be from another universe, would you?

50:14.348 --> 50:15.724
<i>What's he doing?</i>

50:15.807 --> 50:18.977
<i>-I don't know. Looks like he's charging.
</i>-I don't like this. Just web him.

50:31.949 --> 50:35.202
<i>Go left! Left, dude, left!
Left! Go! Left! Yes!</i>

50:35.285 --> 50:39.164
<i>What are you talking about? Right.
Go to the right! Right! Right!</i>

50:39.248 --> 50:43.001
<i>- He means right. Don't listen to him.
- </i>-This is not helping!

50:49.508 --> 50:52.302
Oh, no, no, no.
What happened? Peter? Peter.

50:59.935 --> 51:00.936
Whoa!

51:01.019 --> 51:05.524
Peter, it's me, Flint Marko. You remember?

51:05.607 --> 51:08.777
-Uh, I'm Peter, but I'm not your Peter.
-What do you mean, you're not my Peter?

51:08.861 --> 51:12.865
-What the hell is going on?
-I'll explain, but first, can you help me?

51:12.948 --> 51:14.825
-Okay.
-You try to surround him,

51:14.908 --> 51:16.952
and I'll pull the plug.
All right, let's go!

51:31.175 --> 51:33.969
I can't hold him much longer.

51:34.928 --> 51:36.555
I got it, I got it!

52:04.166 --> 52:06.460
Different Peter. Weird.

52:06.543 --> 52:09.588
-Thanks. Sorry.
-Don't worry about it.

52:17.888 --> 52:19.348
I got my body back.

52:20.224 --> 52:21.308
Hey. Um...

52:22.017 --> 52:25.771
This is gonna sound really crazy,
but, uh, this isn't your universe.

52:25.854 --> 52:27.481
-Another universe?
-Uh-huh.

52:27.564 --> 52:29.233
-What?
-That's what I was feeling.

52:30.067 --> 52:32.194
The power, it's different.

52:33.946 --> 52:34.947
I like it.

52:37.157 --> 52:40.536
-Easy, buddy.
-It's actually my fault that you're here.

52:40.619 --> 52:43.705
Like, the universe or the woods?

52:44.540 --> 52:45.457
I hate the woods.

52:45.541 --> 52:47.459
I meant the universe, sir.

52:47.543 --> 52:50.921
So, what, y'all just gonna stand here
and act like I ain't butt-ass naked?

52:51.004 --> 52:53.215
-I am.
-Uh, no, no. Uh--

52:53.298 --> 52:54.299
I, uh...

53:06.270 --> 53:08.939
What was that?
What did you just do to him?

53:09.022 --> 53:10.732
-No. It's okay.
-Did you kill him?

53:10.816 --> 53:13.193
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
I can explain everything. Trust me.

53:13.277 --> 53:16.029
-Please, just trust me.
-I don't trust you. I don't know you.

53:18.115 --> 53:20.242
Ugh. What is this?

53:21.577 --> 53:23.161
You picked the wrong side.

53:25.831 --> 53:26.999
Connors?

53:28.500 --> 53:30.669
Wait. You know this creature?

53:30.752 --> 53:33.797
No, no, no.
Not a creature. A man.

53:33.881 --> 53:36.091
Whoa. The same universes.

53:36.175 --> 53:40.220
Dr Curt Connors. He was a scientist
at Oscorp when I worked there.

53:40.304 --> 53:42.347
A brilliant scientist.

53:42.431 --> 53:44.057
Until he turned himself into a lizard.

53:44.141 --> 53:46.268
Then he tried to turn
the whole city into lizards.

53:46.351 --> 53:48.770
-It was crazy.
-It wasn't crazy, Max.

53:48.854 --> 53:50.981
It was the next step in human evolution.

53:51.064 --> 53:53.150
-The dinosaur can talk. Right.
-Lizard.

53:53.233 --> 53:54.818
What happened to you?

53:54.902 --> 53:58.655
Last I recall, you had bad teeth,
glasses and a comb-over.

53:58.739 --> 54:00.532
Did you get a makeover?

54:01.366 --> 54:03.869
You know I can give you a real makeover.

54:03.952 --> 54:05.329
Let me guess, into a lizard?

54:05.412 --> 54:07.998
-Exactly.
-Would you two just shut up?

54:08.081 --> 54:09.791
-Where are we?
-It's complicated.

54:09.875 --> 54:12.503
-A wizard's dungeon.
-Wizard's dungeon?

54:12.586 --> 54:16.256
There's no real way to sugar-coat that.
It's literally the dungeon of a wizard.

54:16.340 --> 54:17.841
You can keep your magic.

54:19.009 --> 54:21.637
I want a taste of that energy I just felt.

54:25.098 --> 54:28.060
-Oh, Peter, hey.
-Did those guys come through yet?

54:28.143 --> 54:30.145
There should be an electric guy
and a sand guy.

54:30.229 --> 54:32.773
Yeah, they're all here and locked up.

54:32.856 --> 54:35.776
Perfect. I'm gonna just stay here
and try and fix some of this damage

54:35.859 --> 54:37.611
so they don't blame it on me again.

54:37.694 --> 54:40.030
<i>-Okay.
</i>-But, hey, I, uh...

54:41.031 --> 54:43.742
I couldn't do any of this without you,
so thank you.

54:43.825 --> 54:44.660
<i>Of course.</i>

54:45.410 --> 54:48.038
Hey, ask him
if this is like a tree monster

54:48.121 --> 54:50.499
or like a scientist
that turned into a tree.

54:50.582 --> 54:52.209
It's just a tree, man.

54:52.793 --> 54:54.002
Just a tree.

55:10.686 --> 55:14.523
<i>Coward. We have a new world to conquer.</i>

55:16.483 --> 55:17.943
<i>You make me sick.</i>

55:18.026 --> 55:19.820
Leave me alone, please.

55:19.903 --> 55:22.531
<i>Hiding in the shadows.</i>

55:23.073 --> 55:25.325
<i>Hiding from who you truly are.</i>

55:25.409 --> 55:28.954
-No.
<i>-You can't escape yourself.</i>

55:44.928 --> 55:47.181
- Hey, May.
<i>- Hey, Peter. I'm at work,</i>

55:47.264 --> 55:50.601
<i>and, um, one of the guys
you're looking for just walked in.</i>

55:59.651 --> 56:02.154
May? Where's May? Thank you.

56:05.532 --> 56:06.366
May.

56:07.868 --> 56:10.245
Ah. Hey, here he is.

56:10.329 --> 56:13.582
Norman, this is my nephew.

56:15.125 --> 56:17.711
Norman Osborn? I thought that you were--

56:17.794 --> 56:21.381
I saw Spider-Man in an ad for this place.

56:22.341 --> 56:24.218
And I thought he could help me.

56:24.843 --> 56:26.136
But you're not him.

56:26.220 --> 56:28.555
Wait, so you want Spider-Man's help?

56:28.639 --> 56:30.349
He just wandered in.

56:33.268 --> 56:35.145
I didn't know where else to go.

56:36.647 --> 56:38.690
Someone's living in my house.

56:40.442 --> 56:42.277
Oscorp doesn't exist.

56:44.154 --> 56:45.280
My son...

56:49.326 --> 56:52.287
Sometimes I'm not myself.

56:53.705 --> 56:56.875
-I'm... someone else.
-Mm-hm.

56:56.959 --> 56:59.419
And every time he's in control,
I can't remember.

56:59.503 --> 57:01.797
-Who's in control?
-And now I'm here--

57:01.880 --> 57:05.050
- Who's in control?
- I don't know what's going on.

57:05.133 --> 57:08.720
-Okay, it's okay.
-And I don't-- Doesn't make sense.

57:09.805 --> 57:11.598
He's lost.

57:11.682 --> 57:15.227
And I don't mean just in the cosmos.
I mean in his mind.

57:18.230 --> 57:19.398
Are they all like this?

57:20.357 --> 57:21.400
-Yeah.
-Yeah?

57:21.483 --> 57:24.862
They all have their own mental
or physical issues.

57:24.945 --> 57:27.865
Oh, well, he needs help,
and maybe they all do.

57:28.782 --> 57:31.994
Wait, you don't mean--?
No, May, this isn't my problem.

57:32.077 --> 57:33.996
Peter, not your problem?

57:34.079 --> 57:34.913
Hmm?

57:34.997 --> 57:38.500
May, their chance of getting help is
way better back where they came from.

57:39.626 --> 57:43.422
Sending them home, that's the best thing
that we can do for them.

57:43.505 --> 57:45.757
For them? Or for yourself?

57:48.844 --> 57:52.097
Look around you. This is what we do.

57:52.181 --> 57:56.018
-We help people.
-This is what's best for them.

57:56.977 --> 57:57.978
Trust me.

58:03.775 --> 58:06.361
I'm now joined by supervisor Walter Burke,

58:06.445 --> 58:09.156
who was at the scene
of tonight's disturbance.

58:09.239 --> 58:13.202
Mr Burke, you're saying
you saw Spider-Man, with your own eyes,

58:13.285 --> 58:15.621
destroying multiple power lines?

58:15.787 --> 58:17.706
<i>Uh... Yes. Yes, sir, he did.</i>

58:18.582 --> 58:19.750
There you have it, folks.

58:19.833 --> 58:22.377
Firsthand, from an unimpeachable witness,

58:22.461 --> 58:26.048
the Teen Terror attacking
our electrical grid.

58:26.131 --> 58:29.635
<i>-Yeah, he was talking to the Dirt Man.
</i>-Beg your pardon?

58:29.718 --> 58:33.305
<i>Yeah, he was talking to the Dirt Man
before they worked together</i>

58:33.388 --> 58:37.643
<i>to make the Power Monster disappear
with what appeared to be a sparkle web.</i>

58:37.726 --> 58:39.478
<i>All right. Yep. Thank you very much.</i>

58:39.561 --> 58:41.438
Well, that, uh...

58:41.522 --> 58:44.024
We'll have to circle back
and confirm this, folks.

58:44.107 --> 58:48.946
I'll talk to my producer to see if we can
find out what's in Mr Burke's thermos.

58:49.571 --> 58:53.283
<i>But the fact remains,
Spider-Man is a menace.</i>

58:54.201 --> 58:58.413
We'll be right back after a brief word
from <i>Daily Bugle</i> Supplements.

58:58.497 --> 59:01.291
The only other daily fix you need.

59:01.375 --> 59:02.417
And we're out.

59:05.420 --> 59:06.255
What?

59:09.508 --> 59:10.676
I got eyes on him.

59:10.759 --> 59:12.970
<i>-He's with his aunt and some guy.
</i>-You sure?

59:13.053 --> 59:15.889
<i>-They're just leaving the shelter.
</i>-Okay. Don't lose him.

59:26.775 --> 59:29.903
Thanks, May. Hope to see you again.

59:29.987 --> 59:33.907
Hey. He trusts you. So do I.

59:36.076 --> 59:37.327
Thanks for cleaning my suit.

59:38.537 --> 59:39.413
See you later.

59:41.957 --> 59:44.751
-Guys, this is Mr Osborn.
-Hey, it's "doctor."

59:44.835 --> 59:47.087
Sorry. Dr Osborn, these are my friends.

59:47.171 --> 59:48.505
This is Ned and MJ.

59:49.173 --> 59:52.843
-Mary Jane?
-It's Michelle Jones, actually.

59:54.428 --> 59:55.762
Fascinating.

01:00:00.017 --> 01:00:02.102
Do you think there are other Ned Leedses?

01:00:15.532 --> 01:00:16.825
Octavius?

01:00:20.913 --> 01:00:22.122
Osborn?

01:00:23.123 --> 01:00:24.374
What happened to you?

01:00:24.458 --> 01:00:25.584
What happened to--?

01:00:27.044 --> 01:00:29.796
-You're the walking corpse.
-What do you mean?

01:00:29.880 --> 01:00:32.424
You died, Norman.

01:00:32.508 --> 01:00:34.092
Years ago.

01:00:35.052 --> 01:00:36.637
You're insane.

01:00:36.720 --> 01:00:37.721
God, I love it here.

01:00:37.804 --> 01:00:41.141
What are you talking about?
He's standing right there.

01:00:41.225 --> 01:00:42.309
- He's not--
- Dead.

01:00:43.393 --> 01:00:46.104
They both died, fighting Spider-Man.

01:00:49.650 --> 01:00:51.985
It was all over the news.

01:00:52.069 --> 01:00:56.907
Green Goblin, impaled
by the glider you flew around on.

01:00:57.574 --> 01:01:01.620
And a couple of years later, you, Doc Ock,

01:01:01.703 --> 01:01:04.748
-drowned in the river with your machine.
-Nonsense.

01:01:05.582 --> 01:01:10.045
Spider-Man was trying to stop
my fusion reactor, so I stopped him.

01:01:10.796 --> 01:01:14.383
I had him by the throat, and then I...

01:01:19.388 --> 01:01:20.722
And then I was here.

01:01:20.806 --> 01:01:22.891
Ah, please.
Let me tell you something.

01:01:22.975 --> 01:01:25.018
I was whupping Spider-Man's ass.

01:01:25.102 --> 01:01:27.646
He'll tell you.
And then he caused an overload.

01:01:27.729 --> 01:01:29.940
I was stuck in the grid, absorbing data.

01:01:30.023 --> 01:01:32.401
I was about to turn
into pure energy, and then...

01:01:32.484 --> 01:01:33.402
And then, uh...

01:01:34.486 --> 01:01:36.530
And then-- Oh, shit.

01:01:37.906 --> 01:01:42.286
-I was about to die.
-Max, do you know? Do I die?

01:01:45.497 --> 01:01:47.833
-Oh, great. You caught another one.
-No, wait, Strange.

01:01:47.916 --> 01:01:49.585
He's not dangerous.

01:01:51.545 --> 01:01:52.921
It's okay. Um...

01:01:55.716 --> 01:01:56.633
What is that?

01:01:57.217 --> 01:01:59.928
It's an ancient relic.
The Macchina di Kadavus.

01:02:00.012 --> 01:02:03.307
I've trapped your corrupted spell inside,
and once I finish the proper ritual,

01:02:03.390 --> 01:02:07.436
it'll reverse the spell and send
these guys back to their universes.

01:02:07.519 --> 01:02:10.022
And then what? We perish?

01:02:10.105 --> 01:02:11.815
No. No, thanks. I'll pass on that.

01:02:11.899 --> 01:02:14.902
Let me out of here. Peter!

01:02:15.485 --> 01:02:18.780
Strange, we can't send them back. Not yet.

01:02:19.531 --> 01:02:20.365
Why?

01:02:22.242 --> 01:02:25.621
- Well, some of these guys are gonna die.
- Parker.

01:02:26.330 --> 01:02:28.040
It's their fate.

01:02:29.124 --> 01:02:30.501
Come on, have a heart.

01:02:32.794 --> 01:02:35.380
In the grand calculus of the multiverse,

01:02:36.006 --> 01:02:39.801
their sacrifice means infinitely more
than their lives.

01:02:45.599 --> 01:02:46.683
I'm sorry, kid.

01:02:47.893 --> 01:02:50.229
If they die, they die.

01:03:04.201 --> 01:03:05.202
Peter!

01:03:18.841 --> 01:03:19.800
Don't.

01:03:22.678 --> 01:03:24.847
-What are you doing?
-Peter, you gotta go. Go!

01:03:24.930 --> 01:03:25.931
-Okay.
-Get out of here.

01:03:28.267 --> 01:03:30.018
This is why I never had kids.

01:03:44.491 --> 01:03:45.826
-Give me the box.
-No.

01:03:47.202 --> 01:03:48.161
Whoa!

01:04:04.303 --> 01:04:05.679
Oh, my God, I'm dead.

01:04:05.762 --> 01:04:08.682
You're not dead, you've just been
separated from your physical form.

01:04:08.765 --> 01:04:10.726
My physical-- What?

01:04:11.643 --> 01:04:13.478
How are you doing that?

01:04:13.562 --> 01:04:17.149
-I have no idea.
-You should not be able to do that.

01:04:17.232 --> 01:04:18.692
This feels amazing.

01:04:29.745 --> 01:04:31.705
One of the coolest things
that's happened to me,

01:04:31.788 --> 01:04:33.248
but don't ever do that again.

01:04:39.922 --> 01:04:41.381
Hey! Get off of me!

01:05:07.574 --> 01:05:08.951
<i> ♪ ...la, la, la ♪</i>

01:05:09.034 --> 01:05:11.745
<i>♪ 'Tis the season to be jolly ♪</i>

01:05:11.828 --> 01:05:14.039
<i>♪ Fa, la, la, la, la, la, la-- ♪</i>

01:05:30.013 --> 01:05:31.014
What is this place?

01:05:31.098 --> 01:05:33.934
The Mirror Dimension,
where I'm in control.

01:05:43.110 --> 01:05:45.612
Strange, stop!
Can we just talk about this?

01:05:45.696 --> 01:05:48.699
Parker, don't you realise
that in the multiverse,

01:05:48.782 --> 01:05:53.370
there are an infinite number of people
who know Peter Parker is Spider-Man?

01:05:53.453 --> 01:05:56.331
And if that spell gets loose,
they're all coming here.

01:05:56.415 --> 01:05:59.168
I know, I get it,
but we can't just send them home to die.

01:05:59.251 --> 01:06:00.460
It's their fate.

01:06:01.211 --> 01:06:04.131
You can't change that any more
than you could change who they are.

01:06:04.214 --> 01:06:07.426
What if we could?
What if we could change their fate?

01:06:09.052 --> 01:06:10.596
Whoa. What are you doing?

01:06:15.726 --> 01:06:17.561
I'm not giving you the-- Whoa!

01:06:28.405 --> 01:06:29.656
Give me that back!

01:06:50.594 --> 01:06:52.846
Wait a minute.
Is that an Archimedean Spiral?

01:06:52.930 --> 01:06:55.349
The dimension is just geometry?
You're great at geometry.

01:06:55.432 --> 01:06:57.017
You can do geometry.

01:06:58.894 --> 01:07:00.812
Square the radius. Divide by pi.

01:07:00.896 --> 01:07:03.607
- Plot points along the curve.
- It's over, Parker.

01:07:04.107 --> 01:07:05.734
I'll come pick you up when it's done.

01:07:08.612 --> 01:07:09.655
Hey, Strange.

01:07:10.531 --> 01:07:12.074
You know what's cooler than magic?

01:07:16.161 --> 01:07:18.455
-Math.
-Don't do this.

01:07:21.458 --> 01:07:23.418
-Ow.
-I'm sorry, sir, but...

01:07:28.048 --> 01:07:29.299
I have to try.

01:07:32.135 --> 01:07:34.972
-What happened?
-I had a fight with Strange and I won.

01:07:35.055 --> 01:07:36.890
- What?
- I stole his ring thing.

01:07:36.974 --> 01:07:37.891
Whoa.

01:07:37.975 --> 01:07:41.937
I was swinging, and then I went
through this massive mirror thing,

01:07:42.020 --> 01:07:43.647
-and then I was back--
-Where is he?

01:07:43.730 --> 01:07:45.566
He's trapped,
but I'm not sure for how long.

01:07:45.649 --> 01:07:47.651
You could have left us to die.

01:07:47.734 --> 01:07:49.194
Why didn't you?

01:07:49.278 --> 01:07:50.737
'Cause that's not who he is.

01:07:54.116 --> 01:07:56.159
I think I can help you guys.

01:07:56.243 --> 01:07:58.954
If I can fix what happened to you,
then when you go back,

01:07:59.037 --> 01:08:02.457
things will be different,
and you might not die fighting Spider-Man.

01:08:02.541 --> 01:08:04.835
- What do you mean?
- Our technology is advanced--

01:08:04.918 --> 01:08:09.381
I can help you. You know,
I'm something of a scientist myself.

01:08:11.425 --> 01:08:13.260
Octavius knows what I can do.

01:08:13.343 --> 01:08:15.888
Fix? You mean like a dog?

01:08:15.971 --> 01:08:17.305
I refuse.

01:08:17.389 --> 01:08:20.058
I can't promise you guys anything,
but at least this way,

01:08:20.142 --> 01:08:22.352
you get to go home and have a chance.

01:08:22.435 --> 01:08:23.604
A second chance.

01:08:24.270 --> 01:08:26.106
Isn't that worth trying?

01:08:26.189 --> 01:08:29.818
Trust me, Peter,
when you try to fix people,

01:08:29.902 --> 01:08:32.613
there are always consequences.

01:08:32.696 --> 01:08:35.908
You don't have to come.
I also didn't know that you could talk.

01:08:35.991 --> 01:08:37.451
But if you stay here...

01:08:37.533 --> 01:08:39.912
you'll have to deal
with the wizard.

01:08:39.995 --> 01:08:44.499
Ah. So we go along or die.
Not much of a choice, is it?

01:08:44.582 --> 01:08:46.001
I just wanna go home.

01:08:46.084 --> 01:08:49.796
I, myself, don't wanna be killed,
especially by a guy dressed

01:08:49.880 --> 01:08:53.383
like Dungeons & Dragons,
so, what's your plan?

01:08:54.843 --> 01:08:56.511
I have it all under control.

01:09:00.057 --> 01:09:02.059
What are we gonna do about this thing?

01:09:02.142 --> 01:09:04.685
Uh, we need to find
somewhere safe for it, right?

01:09:04.770 --> 01:09:06.979
- You gotta take it.
- Wait, what?

01:09:07.064 --> 01:09:10.399
If something bad happens,
you just push this and then it's over.

01:09:10.484 --> 01:09:12.277
We're not gonna leave you.

01:09:12.361 --> 01:09:13.612
You can't. It's dangerous.

01:09:13.694 --> 01:09:15.697
-You have done enough.
-We're in this together.

01:09:15.781 --> 01:09:19.326
I know we're in this together, Ned,
but I can't do this if you're in danger.

01:09:19.408 --> 01:09:22.162
Okay? So for me, MJ,
please just take this.

01:09:25.122 --> 01:09:27.042
-Please.
-Fine.

01:09:27.709 --> 01:09:28.961
- Thank you.
- But, Peter,

01:09:29.044 --> 01:09:31.296
if I don't hear from you,
I'm pressing the button.

01:09:31.380 --> 01:09:33.590
-Sure.
-Okay. And I will do it.

01:09:35.050 --> 01:09:36.718
Yeah, we all believe you, Michelle.

01:09:36.801 --> 01:09:39.680
No way that's his girlfriend. No way.

01:09:39.763 --> 01:09:42.390
-She'll do it.
-Absolutely, she will.

01:09:43.809 --> 01:09:46.645
-Okay. See you later.
-Be safe.

01:09:46.728 --> 01:09:47.938
- You too.
- Okay.

01:09:49.898 --> 01:09:50.899
Whoa.

01:09:52.149 --> 01:09:52.984
Okay.

01:09:55.279 --> 01:09:56.738
-Be careful, okay?
-Yeah. You too.

01:10:04.705 --> 01:10:05.539
So, uh...

01:10:07.165 --> 01:10:08.458
who's coming with me?

01:10:12.754 --> 01:10:13.589
Well, I'm in.

01:10:14.298 --> 01:10:16.717
But if this goes sideways...

01:10:17.968 --> 01:10:19.970
I'm gonna fry you from the inside out.

01:10:32.399 --> 01:10:35.277
My client has nothing to do
with the missing technology.

01:10:35.360 --> 01:10:37.487
He's a law-abiding citizen.
He has nothing to hide.

01:10:38.030 --> 01:10:39.031
That's right.

01:10:52.961 --> 01:10:55.797
<i>- Where's Connors?
- </i>-<i>He wants to stay in the truck.</i>

01:10:55.881 --> 01:10:58.675
- <i>Okay.
- </i>-Mr Hogan, is something wrong?

01:11:00.010 --> 01:11:01.011
Happy.

01:11:02.179 --> 01:11:04.181
Stop sweating.

01:11:05.057 --> 01:11:06.225
How do you do that?

01:11:07.392 --> 01:11:10.103
-Yeah?
-I feel bad using Happy's place like this.

01:11:10.187 --> 01:11:12.189
No, no, no. He'll get over it.

01:11:13.065 --> 01:11:16.151
<i>New Yorkers oppose
the Statue of Liberty renovation...</i>

01:11:16.235 --> 01:11:17.069
Oh, sorry.

01:11:18.111 --> 01:11:20.197
So this is your plan, Peter? Hmm?

01:11:20.280 --> 01:11:21.615
No lab, no facilities?

01:11:21.698 --> 01:11:24.409
Just performing miracles
in a condominium? Hmm?

01:11:24.493 --> 01:11:27.704
What, you gonna cook us some cures
and some frozen burritos in a microwave?

01:11:27.788 --> 01:11:30.791
-I could go for a burrito.
-He's gonna kill us all.

01:11:30.874 --> 01:11:32.167
Well, let's hope not.

01:11:32.918 --> 01:11:35.045
-You're up first, Doc.
-What?

01:11:35.128 --> 01:11:36.713
Hey, I told you, I don't need fixing.

01:11:37.506 --> 01:11:39.550
I don't need fixing!

01:11:39.633 --> 01:11:43.971
Especially by a teenager using scraps
from a bachelor's junk drawer.

01:11:44.054 --> 01:11:46.640
Nah, nah, nah.
He got something back there.

01:11:47.182 --> 01:11:49.518
I can feel it. That weird energy.

01:11:51.019 --> 01:11:53.522
-What the hell is that?
-It's a fabricator.

01:11:54.147 --> 01:11:57.651
It can analyse, design,
construct basically anything.

01:11:58.652 --> 01:12:00.904
I thought that was
the tanning bed Happy broke.

01:12:03.782 --> 01:12:04.825
Look at that.

01:12:12.207 --> 01:12:13.667
He's gonna kill us all.

01:12:21.758 --> 01:12:22.885
Oh!

01:12:22.968 --> 01:12:24.303
What's going on there?

01:12:24.928 --> 01:12:28.098
So the chip in the back of Doc's
neck was designed to protect his brain

01:12:28.182 --> 01:12:32.227
from the AI system that's controlling
these tentacles, but if you look here...

01:12:34.271 --> 01:12:35.105
the chip is fried.

01:12:35.189 --> 01:12:37.441
So rather than him being
in control of the tentacles,

01:12:37.524 --> 01:12:39.610
the tentacles are now in control of him.

01:12:39.693 --> 01:12:44.781
Which, I guess, explains why
he is so miserable all the time.

01:12:44.990 --> 01:12:48.702
But, if you look here,
if I can introduce self--

01:12:48.785 --> 01:12:51.705
Self-healing composite circuitry.

01:12:53.123 --> 01:12:56.752
Exactly. So, theoretically,
I mean, if this were to work,

01:12:56.835 --> 01:12:58.795
he would go back to the way he was.

01:13:07.179 --> 01:13:08.013
Thirsty?

01:13:11.308 --> 01:13:12.726
Well, yes, I am thirsty.

01:13:13.477 --> 01:13:14.937
Fresh water or salt?

01:13:15.938 --> 01:13:17.773
You know, because you're an octopus.

01:13:19.650 --> 01:13:20.817
What?

01:13:22.236 --> 01:13:23.612
Fresh water it is.

01:13:24.738 --> 01:13:25.906
Look at this place.

01:13:26.782 --> 01:13:29.993
-And all the possibilities.
-What, this condo?

01:13:30.077 --> 01:13:33.163
Yeah, yeah, the condo.
I love the whole open floor plan. No.

01:13:33.247 --> 01:13:35.457
Nah, man, I'm talking about the world.

01:13:37.042 --> 01:13:38.335
I kind of like who I am here.

01:13:40.212 --> 01:13:41.839
And all that power back there...

01:13:43.006 --> 01:13:44.508
I could be so much more.

01:13:45.759 --> 01:13:46.969
So why'd you come along?

01:13:47.052 --> 01:13:49.847
I have a daughter, and I want to see her.

01:13:49.930 --> 01:13:52.057
But he's not gonna send anyone home

01:13:52.140 --> 01:13:54.977
till he's finished
his little science project back there.

01:13:55.519 --> 01:13:56.770
You trust him?

01:13:56.854 --> 01:13:58.146
I don't trust anyone.

01:13:59.648 --> 01:14:01.733
-How'd you end up like that, anyway?
-Oh.

01:14:03.151 --> 01:14:04.903
The place where I worked at,

01:14:04.987 --> 01:14:09.741
they were experimenting with electricity
created by living organisms, and then...

01:14:10.742 --> 01:14:12.953
I fell into a vat of electric eels.

01:14:13.036 --> 01:14:16.039
You're kidding.
I fell into a supercollider.

01:14:16.123 --> 01:14:16.957
Damn.

01:14:18.083 --> 01:14:19.751
Gotta be careful where you fall.

01:14:20.627 --> 01:14:21.962
Remarkable.

01:14:23.922 --> 01:14:25.841
The technology and you.

01:14:28.677 --> 01:14:30.012
When all this is over,

01:14:30.762 --> 01:14:35.267
if you need a job and you're willing
to commute to another universe...

01:14:41.857 --> 01:14:44.776
It worked. That totally worked!

01:14:44.860 --> 01:14:48.071
- I got it. I did it. Will you send him up?
- Here we go.

01:14:49.823 --> 01:14:51.283
- Sorry.
- Hold on, Doc.

01:14:51.366 --> 01:14:53.952
Oh, will these humiliations never cease?

01:14:54.036 --> 01:14:57.039
You, keep your science-fair project
away from me!

01:14:57.122 --> 01:14:58.749
It'll work. Have faith.

01:14:58.832 --> 01:15:01.835
Says the reckless fool
who turned himself into a monster.

01:15:03.045 --> 01:15:04.963
Please stop moving your head.

01:15:05.047 --> 01:15:08.509
- Hold still.
- Don't you dare.

01:15:12.429 --> 01:15:16.683
I swear, when I get out of this,
we're gonna rip you a new--

01:15:21.188 --> 01:15:22.189
Doc?

01:15:28.111 --> 01:15:28.946
Doc?

01:15:31.073 --> 01:15:31.907
Doc?

01:15:33.158 --> 01:15:36.119
Dr Octav--

01:15:41.208 --> 01:15:42.376
It's so quiet.

01:15:46.296 --> 01:15:49.132
Those voices inside my head...

01:15:54.513 --> 01:15:55.806
I'd almost forgotten.

01:15:57.349 --> 01:15:58.308
Otto.

01:15:59.643 --> 01:16:01.395
Yes. Norman.

01:16:07.734 --> 01:16:08.944
It's me.

01:16:11.196 --> 01:16:12.531
Would you look at that?

01:16:33.135 --> 01:16:36.263
I'm grateful, dear boy. Truly.

01:16:36.346 --> 01:16:37.639
Yeah, you're welcome.

01:16:38.473 --> 01:16:39.474
How can I help?

01:16:40.267 --> 01:16:42.352
<i>This is Peter. Leave a message.</i>

01:16:43.770 --> 01:16:46.899
Yeah, Peter, this is Happy.
I accessed my doorbell camera.

01:16:46.982 --> 01:16:49.193
Who are those guys, huh? Is that a cyborg?

01:16:49.276 --> 01:16:51.653
You bring a cyborg
with robot legs into my house?

01:16:51.737 --> 01:16:54.239
Was one of the guys made of mud?
What's going on? Call me.

01:17:03.457 --> 01:17:04.958
How does it feel, Norman?

01:17:06.251 --> 01:17:07.794
You're about to become whole again.

01:17:09.296 --> 01:17:10.923
No more darker half.

01:17:11.924 --> 01:17:12.758
Just you.

01:17:14.009 --> 01:17:15.010
Just me.

01:17:24.436 --> 01:17:25.521
Okay. Um...

01:17:27.105 --> 01:17:28.565
It just goes right here. This...

01:17:30.400 --> 01:17:31.902
That should be drawing power now.

01:17:31.985 --> 01:17:35.697
I'll come back in a second to check on it,
but keep an eye on the lights.

01:17:35.781 --> 01:17:38.700
When they're all green,
the electricity in your body's dissipated.

01:17:38.784 --> 01:17:42.538
Well, not all of the electricity. You need
electricity for your brain to function.

01:17:42.621 --> 01:17:43.997
Your nervous system is...

01:17:44.623 --> 01:17:46.875
I'm not really sure
why I'm explaining electricity to you.

01:17:46.959 --> 01:17:49.795
-Hmm. Yeah, can I ask you a question?
-Sure.

01:17:49.878 --> 01:17:51.004
Are these your Legos?

01:17:53.131 --> 01:17:55.300
Uh, I gotta go. I'll be back.

01:18:01.181 --> 01:18:03.684
- Something feels off.
- What do you mean?

01:18:04.893 --> 01:18:07.187
-I don't like this.
-Leave it alone.

01:18:07.271 --> 01:18:11.108
The sooner you guys get through this,
the sooner we go home.

01:18:18.949 --> 01:18:21.243
-Well, where is he?
-He's inside.

01:18:21.326 --> 01:18:22.995
And yet here we are, outside.

01:18:23.078 --> 01:18:25.080
Did you not hear me say, "Don't lose him"?

01:18:25.163 --> 01:18:27.082
I want incriminating footage
of Spider-Man.

01:18:27.165 --> 01:18:29.126
I called Damage Control.
They're on their way.

01:18:29.209 --> 01:18:30.752
And so it begins.

01:18:30.836 --> 01:18:32.754
Place is about to be swarming with cops.

01:18:51.857 --> 01:18:53.192
Peter?

01:18:54.610 --> 01:18:55.485
What's wrong?

01:18:56.862 --> 01:18:57.696
I don't know.

01:18:58.864 --> 01:18:59.698
May?

01:19:05.537 --> 01:19:07.080
What is it, Peter?

01:19:14.087 --> 01:19:15.923
What's happening?

01:19:22.387 --> 01:19:24.014
Why are you looking at me like that?

01:19:39.738 --> 01:19:44.493
That's some neat trick,
that sense of yours.

01:19:44.576 --> 01:19:48.080
- Norman?
- Norman's on sabbatical, honey.

01:19:48.830 --> 01:19:51.041
- The hell?
- The Goblin.

01:19:52.334 --> 01:19:57.047
"No more darker half"? Did you really
think that I'd let that happen?

01:19:57.965 --> 01:20:01.426
That I'd let you take away my power
just because you're blind

01:20:01.510 --> 01:20:04.888
-to what true power can bring you?
-You don't know me.

01:20:04.972 --> 01:20:06.181
Don't I?

01:20:09.434 --> 01:20:12.187
I saw how she trapped you,

01:20:12.271 --> 01:20:14.898
fighting her holy moral mission.

01:20:17.651 --> 01:20:19.820
We don't need you to save us.

01:20:19.903 --> 01:20:21.947
We don't need to be fixed.

01:20:25.492 --> 01:20:27.452
These are not curses.

01:20:29.288 --> 01:20:30.455
They're gifts.

01:20:31.832 --> 01:20:33.834
- Norman, no.
- Quiet, lapdog.

01:20:33.917 --> 01:20:36.503
-You don't know what you're talking about.
-I've watched you

01:20:36.587 --> 01:20:40.382
from deep behind Norman's cowardly eyes.

01:20:41.049 --> 01:20:46.388
Struggling to have everything you want

01:20:46.471 --> 01:20:50.017
while the world tries to make you choose.

01:20:52.186 --> 01:20:55.439
Gods don't have to choose.

01:20:57.566 --> 01:20:59.026
We take.

01:20:59.109 --> 01:21:00.569
May, run.

01:21:23.884 --> 01:21:25.010
Oh, my God.

01:21:25.886 --> 01:21:28.972
-What have you done?
-I liked you better before.

01:21:38.398 --> 01:21:41.318
Up here! He's up there.
It's the guy from the bridge.

01:22:04.341 --> 01:22:05.425
Did you see that?

01:22:31.994 --> 01:22:33.078
No, you don't!

01:22:42.504 --> 01:22:44.840
Strong enough to have it all.

01:22:48.218 --> 01:22:49.595
Too weak to take it!

01:23:25.214 --> 01:23:26.507
Now I got you.

01:23:28.675 --> 01:23:31.011
I told you, there'd be consequences!

01:23:49.238 --> 01:23:52.699
Your weakness, Peter, is morality.

01:23:53.242 --> 01:23:57.120
It's choking you. Can't you feel it?

01:24:05.504 --> 01:24:06.797
It didn't work.

01:24:07.673 --> 01:24:09.842
Norman was right.

01:24:09.925 --> 01:24:13.595
He got it from you,
that pathetic sickness.

01:24:18.308 --> 01:24:19.935
You tried to fix me.

01:24:20.811 --> 01:24:21.979
May, go.

01:24:22.062 --> 01:24:24.273
Now I'm gonna fix you.

01:24:28.318 --> 01:24:29.403
May, run, please.

01:24:32.906 --> 01:24:34.241
May!

01:24:40.831 --> 01:24:42.875
Peter, Peter, Peter.

01:24:42.958 --> 01:24:46.044
No good deed goes unpunished.

01:24:46.628 --> 01:24:48.797
You can thank me later.

01:24:54.678 --> 01:24:55.929
No!

01:25:25.834 --> 01:25:26.668
- May?
- Peter.

01:25:26.752 --> 01:25:28.170
May, May, I'm here.

01:25:32.090 --> 01:25:32.925
May.

01:25:33.592 --> 01:25:34.593
May, I'm here.

01:25:35.677 --> 01:25:37.971
-Are you okay? What happened?
-Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

01:25:44.311 --> 01:25:46.313
It's okay. We're okay, right?

01:25:46.396 --> 01:25:48.106
Yeah. Knocked on my ass.

01:25:48.190 --> 01:25:49.316
-Yeah, me too.
-That's all.

01:25:50.067 --> 01:25:53.028
I think I broke my ribs.

01:25:58.408 --> 01:26:00.577
-This is all my fault, May.
-No.

01:26:00.661 --> 01:26:02.621
I should have let Strange send them back.

01:26:02.704 --> 01:26:03.830
You did the right thing.

01:26:04.706 --> 01:26:07.793
They would have been killed.
You did the right thing.

01:26:08.502 --> 01:26:10.546
It's not my responsibility, May.

01:26:12.631 --> 01:26:13.715
Oh.

01:26:14.299 --> 01:26:15.342
What Norman said?

01:26:16.760 --> 01:26:18.679
My moral mission? No.

01:26:18.762 --> 01:26:20.848
-No, May--
-Peter, you listen to me.

01:26:22.224 --> 01:26:23.225
You have a gift.

01:26:24.810 --> 01:26:26.186
You have power.

01:26:27.062 --> 01:26:28.480
And with great power,

01:26:28.564 --> 01:26:32.526
there must also come
great responsibility. Hmm?

01:26:37.281 --> 01:26:38.574
I know.

01:26:38.657 --> 01:26:40.576
Let's get the...out of here.

01:26:40.659 --> 01:26:41.785
Okay, let's go.

01:26:42.995 --> 01:26:44.663
Let me just catch my...

01:27:00.762 --> 01:27:02.764
-What happened? Are you okay?
-I'm okay.

01:27:02.848 --> 01:27:04.600
Yeah, you're okay. What happened?

01:27:06.435 --> 01:27:07.519
Just have to...

01:27:08.687 --> 01:27:09.646
catch my breath.

01:27:09.730 --> 01:27:11.648
Okay, well, catch your breath.
I'm right here.

01:27:11.732 --> 01:27:12.858
We're gonna take our time.

01:27:12.941 --> 01:27:15.944
You catch your breath
and then we'll take you to a doctor, okay?

01:27:34.421 --> 01:27:35.422
Are you okay?

01:27:36.507 --> 01:27:39.384
Somebody help!
I need an ambulance, please! Somebody?

01:27:39.468 --> 01:27:41.386
-What happened?
-Nothing happened.

01:27:42.471 --> 01:27:44.097
You're okay, you're okay.

01:27:45.849 --> 01:27:48.310
Let me just-- Let me catch my breath.

01:27:48.393 --> 01:27:50.270
I'm right here. I'm right here.

01:27:50.854 --> 01:27:51.855
I'm right here.

01:27:58.904 --> 01:27:59.905
You're okay.

01:28:01.573 --> 01:28:02.658
It's just me and you.

01:28:12.876 --> 01:28:13.710
May?

01:28:20.384 --> 01:28:21.218
May?

01:28:27.599 --> 01:28:29.017
Will you look at me, please?

01:28:37.818 --> 01:28:38.652
May.

01:28:39.820 --> 01:28:40.654
May.

01:28:42.656 --> 01:28:43.699
What are you doing, May?

01:28:43.782 --> 01:28:46.660
Please, will you just wake up
and talk to me? Please?

01:29:09.600 --> 01:29:11.310
Get out of the car now! Move!

01:29:17.858 --> 01:29:19.526
Get off, get off, get off me.

01:29:21.862 --> 01:29:22.696
Peter!

01:29:22.779 --> 01:29:24.573
-Run!
-It's just me and you, okay?

01:29:24.656 --> 01:29:26.533
It's just me and you, okay?

01:29:26.617 --> 01:29:28.368
Oh, May, I'm sorry.

01:29:28.452 --> 01:29:29.620
I'm so sorry.

01:29:29.703 --> 01:29:31.371
I'm so, so, so sorry. I love you.

01:29:31.455 --> 01:29:33.916
Parker, come out with your hands up!

01:29:34.583 --> 01:29:37.044
Come out right now,
or we will open fire!

01:29:37.127 --> 01:29:38.086
Run!

01:29:42.007 --> 01:29:44.593
All right, let's go, let's go!
Move in!

01:30:02.319 --> 01:30:03.445
<i>Tragedy.</i>

01:30:07.241 --> 01:30:08.659
<i>What else can I call it?</i>

01:30:09.868 --> 01:30:11.787
<i>What more need be said?</i>

01:30:12.746 --> 01:30:15.290
<i>The damage, the destruction.</i>

01:30:16.083 --> 01:30:17.960
<i>You saw it with your own eyes.</i>

01:30:19.503 --> 01:30:24.424
<i>When will people wake up and realise
that everywhere Spider-Man goes,</i>

01:30:24.508 --> 01:30:27.344
<i>chaos and calamity ensue?</i>

01:30:28.178 --> 01:30:32.266
<i>Everything Spider-Man touches
comes to ruin.</i>

01:30:33.350 --> 01:30:35.352
<i>And we, the innocents,</i>

01:30:36.019 --> 01:30:37.980
<i>are left to pick up the pieces.</i>

01:30:40.482 --> 01:30:42.609
<i>J. Jonah Jameson reporting.</i>

01:30:42.693 --> 01:30:45.779
<i>Good night, and God help us all.</i>

01:31:05.382 --> 01:31:08.760
<i>We are told
that multiple people have been injured,</i>

01:31:08.844 --> 01:31:13.182
<i>and we can confirm
at least one person has been killed.</i>

01:31:13.265 --> 01:31:14.308
Still nothing?

01:31:15.976 --> 01:31:16.852
No.

01:31:32.951 --> 01:31:33.785
I'm gonna press it.

01:31:35.871 --> 01:31:38.498
-What? No, he--
-I know he told me to wait...

01:31:39.958 --> 01:31:42.127
-but I'm gonna do it.
-I just wish--

01:31:42.211 --> 01:31:43.921
I just wish we could see him.

01:31:49.218 --> 01:31:50.302
-Ned?
-Yeah?

01:31:51.345 --> 01:31:52.763
-Do that again.
-Yeah.

01:31:55.224 --> 01:31:56.475
I just wish we could see him.

01:32:00.395 --> 01:32:01.230
Okay.

01:32:01.980 --> 01:32:03.815
I just wish we could see Peter.

01:32:06.360 --> 01:32:08.904
Whoa.

01:32:08.987 --> 01:32:12.533
<i>Lola, </i>you're right. I am magic.

01:32:13.825 --> 01:32:14.660
Is that him?

01:32:15.577 --> 01:32:17.955
-Yeah, yeah, it has to be.
-Peter. Peter!

01:32:18.038 --> 01:32:20.082
- Hey, Peter! Yeah.
- Peter!

01:32:25.337 --> 01:32:26.463
Whoa.

01:32:28.549 --> 01:32:30.092
Hi. Hi.

01:32:30.175 --> 01:32:33.262
No, no, no, it's okay.
It's okay. I'm a nice guy.

01:32:35.931 --> 01:32:37.266
Okay.

01:32:39.852 --> 01:32:42.396
-Who the hell are you?
-I'm Peter Parker.

01:32:42.479 --> 01:32:46.650
-That's not possible.
-I am Spider-Man, in my world.

01:32:46.733 --> 01:32:49.820
But then yesterday, I was--

01:32:51.572 --> 01:32:53.365
I was just here.

01:32:54.950 --> 01:32:56.201
Wow.

01:32:57.828 --> 01:33:01.331
String theory, multidimensional reality...

01:33:02.624 --> 01:33:04.126
and matter displacement.

01:33:04.877 --> 01:33:05.711
All real?

01:33:05.794 --> 01:33:06.795
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

01:33:06.879 --> 01:33:08.088
I knew it.

01:33:09.798 --> 01:33:11.592
This has to be because of the spell.

01:33:12.217 --> 01:33:13.969
The spell? Like magic spell?

01:33:14.052 --> 01:33:15.888
-Uh, there's no spell. No.
-No spell.

01:33:15.971 --> 01:33:17.723
-Magic's real here too?
-I mean--

01:33:17.806 --> 01:33:20.225
-Shut up, Ned. Shut up.
-No, it's not real.

01:33:20.309 --> 01:33:22.853
-There's magicians, but there's no--
-Stop talking.

01:33:22.936 --> 01:33:24.605
Stop. Stop.

01:33:25.397 --> 01:33:26.732
-Prove it.
-Prove what?

01:33:26.815 --> 01:33:30.194
-That you're Peter Parker.
-I don't carry an ID with me, you know?

01:33:30.277 --> 01:33:32.696
Kind of defeats
the whole anonymous superhero thing.

01:33:35.365 --> 01:33:37.534
-Why'd you do that?
-To see if you have the tingle thing.

01:33:37.618 --> 01:33:39.578
I have the tingle thing,
just not for bread.

01:33:39.661 --> 01:33:41.663
Can you not throw the bread again?

01:33:41.747 --> 01:33:43.999
You're a deeply mistrusting person...

01:33:45.709 --> 01:33:46.752
and I respect it.

01:33:52.424 --> 01:33:53.258
Crawl around.

01:33:53.342 --> 01:33:55.260
- Crawl around?
- Yes.

01:33:55.344 --> 01:33:56.929
-No.
-Yes, crawl around.

01:33:57.012 --> 01:33:58.680
- Why do I need to?
- This is not enough.

01:33:58.764 --> 01:34:00.015
-This is plenty.
-No, it's not.

01:34:00.098 --> 01:34:01.767
-Yes, it is. It is.
-No, it's not. Nuh-uh.

01:34:01.850 --> 01:34:04.394
- How do I stick to the ceiling?
- Do it.

01:34:06.230 --> 01:34:10.025
Ned.

01:34:12.694 --> 01:34:16.114
My <i>lola's </i>asking
if you could just get the cobweb there.

01:34:16.198 --> 01:34:18.075
-Since you're, like, up there.
-Yeah.

01:34:26.083 --> 01:34:26.959
Thank you.

01:34:31.880 --> 01:34:32.714
We--

01:34:33.340 --> 01:34:34.174
We good?

01:34:34.258 --> 01:34:35.175
For now.

01:34:35.926 --> 01:34:38.846
So I opened the wrong portal
to the wrong Peter Parker.

01:34:38.929 --> 01:34:41.223
I guess you keep doing it
until we find the real one.

01:34:41.306 --> 01:34:43.225
-Ouch.
-No offence.

01:34:43.892 --> 01:34:45.435
- Okay.
- Okay. You got it.

01:34:47.771 --> 01:34:49.147
Find Peter Parker.

01:34:49.231 --> 01:34:51.275
-What's the thing on his hand?
-Shh.

01:34:51.358 --> 01:34:53.360
Find Peter Parker.

01:34:55.362 --> 01:34:56.905
Find Peter Parker!

01:35:06.290 --> 01:35:07.749
Great, it's just some random guy.

01:35:08.625 --> 01:35:09.501
Hello.

01:35:10.002 --> 01:35:12.629
Um, I hope it's okay,
I just came through this, uh...

01:35:13.630 --> 01:35:15.507
Oh. It just closed.

01:35:17.050 --> 01:35:18.302
You're Peter?

01:35:19.094 --> 01:35:21.305
Yeah. Peter Parker.

01:35:23.432 --> 01:35:25.100
I've seen you two--

01:35:27.561 --> 01:35:28.395
Hi.

01:35:32.649 --> 01:35:35.277
Wait. He's-- He's not your friend.

01:35:48.457 --> 01:35:49.625
Huh.

01:35:51.210 --> 01:35:54.379
Wait. So you're Spider-Man too?
Why didn't you just say that?

01:35:54.463 --> 01:35:56.965
I generally don't go around
advertising it.

01:35:57.049 --> 01:35:59.134
Kind of defeats
the whole anonymous superhero thing.

01:35:59.218 --> 01:36:00.928
-I just said that.
-That's what he just said.

01:36:13.315 --> 01:36:16.860
My <i>lola's </i>asking if you could clean up
the webs you just shot.

01:36:16.944 --> 01:36:18.654
-Oh, sorry, <i>Lola.
</i>-Yes, of course.

01:36:18.737 --> 01:36:20.113
I'm going to bed.

01:36:20.197 --> 01:36:22.449
- Night, <i>Lola.
- </i>-Good night, Ned's <i>lola.</i>

01:36:23.075 --> 01:36:25.410
Uh, this might seem kind of weird,

01:36:25.953 --> 01:36:28.580
but I've been trying to find
your friend ever since I got here.

01:36:30.165 --> 01:36:31.875
I just have this sense...

01:36:33.961 --> 01:36:35.295
that he needs my help.

01:36:35.379 --> 01:36:36.380
Our help.

01:36:38.340 --> 01:36:39.424
He does.

01:36:39.508 --> 01:36:41.218
We don't know where he is.

01:36:41.301 --> 01:36:45.305
And, um, honestly,
right now we're all he really has left.

01:36:46.807 --> 01:36:51.812
Well, uh, is there someplace
that he might go

01:36:51.895 --> 01:36:54.064
that has meaning to him?

01:36:55.566 --> 01:36:59.069
Like a place where he would go to just--?

01:36:59.152 --> 01:37:00.654
Get away from everything?

01:37:03.740 --> 01:37:06.994
For me, it was the top
of the Chrysler Building.

01:37:07.077 --> 01:37:08.328
Empire State.

01:37:08.412 --> 01:37:11.582
-It's just a-- It's a better view.
-That is a sweet view.

01:37:14.376 --> 01:37:15.252
Yes.

01:37:16.295 --> 01:37:19.256
Yeah. I think
I know exactly where that would be.

01:37:55.501 --> 01:37:56.335
I'm sorry.

01:38:04.051 --> 01:38:05.177
Peter, there's...

01:38:06.720 --> 01:38:08.222
There's some people here.

01:38:09.723 --> 01:38:10.557
What?

01:38:19.733 --> 01:38:21.026
Hey, wait, wait! Whoa.

01:38:22.277 --> 01:38:23.195
What...?

01:38:26.240 --> 01:38:27.074
Sorry...

01:38:28.992 --> 01:38:29.952
about May.

01:38:33.664 --> 01:38:38.877
Yeah. Sorry.
I got some understanding

01:38:38.961 --> 01:38:39.837
of what it is you're--

01:38:39.920 --> 01:38:42.548
No, please don't tell me
that you know what I'm going through.

01:38:43.298 --> 01:38:45.050
-Okay.
-She's gone.

01:38:48.095 --> 01:38:49.429
And it's all my fault.

01:38:53.642 --> 01:38:54.935
She died for nothing.

01:38:58.689 --> 01:39:00.649
I'll do what I should have done
in the first place.

01:39:01.275 --> 01:39:02.985
- Peter--
- Please don't.

01:39:04.111 --> 01:39:07.364
You don't belong here. Either of you.
So I'm sending you home.

01:39:08.949 --> 01:39:11.118
Those other guys are
from your worlds, right?

01:39:12.035 --> 01:39:13.537
So you deal with it.

01:39:13.620 --> 01:39:15.539
If they die, if you kill them...

01:39:16.498 --> 01:39:17.332
that's on you.

01:39:18.542 --> 01:39:19.418
It's not my problem.

01:39:20.377 --> 01:39:21.628
I don't care anymore.

01:39:23.046 --> 01:39:23.881
I'm done.

01:39:28.927 --> 01:39:31.221
I'm really sorry
that I dragged you into this.

01:39:34.850 --> 01:39:36.518
But you have to go home now.

01:39:39.062 --> 01:39:39.897
Good luck.

01:39:45.611 --> 01:39:47.362
My uncle Ben was killed.

01:39:49.031 --> 01:39:50.073
It was my fault.

01:39:51.658 --> 01:39:52.534
I lost...

01:39:55.704 --> 01:39:57.456
I lost Gwen, my, um...

01:39:59.082 --> 01:40:00.083
She was my MJ.

01:40:02.961 --> 01:40:04.171
I couldn't save her.

01:40:05.839 --> 01:40:08.217
I'm never gonna be able
to forgive myself for that.

01:40:11.345 --> 01:40:13.222
But I carried on, tried to, um...

01:40:14.431 --> 01:40:16.683
Tried to keep going,
tried to keep being...

01:40:18.435 --> 01:40:20.312
the friendly neighbourhood Spider-Man

01:40:20.395 --> 01:40:22.564
'cause I know that's
what she would've wanted.

01:40:23.398 --> 01:40:26.610
But at some point,
I just stopped pulling my punches.

01:40:30.656 --> 01:40:31.782
I got rageful.

01:40:34.284 --> 01:40:35.577
I got bitter.

01:40:36.995 --> 01:40:41.041
I just don't want you to end up like me.

01:40:42.835 --> 01:40:45.128
The night Ben died...

01:40:46.463 --> 01:40:48.590
I hunted down the man
who I thought did it.

01:40:50.467 --> 01:40:51.760
I wanted him dead.

01:40:54.638 --> 01:40:56.098
I got what I wanted.

01:40:58.559 --> 01:41:00.102
It didn't make it better.

01:41:04.106 --> 01:41:06.316
It took me a long time...

01:41:08.360 --> 01:41:09.987
to learn to get through that darkness.

01:41:13.365 --> 01:41:14.575
I wanna kill him.

01:41:17.411 --> 01:41:18.912
I wanna tear him apart.

01:41:22.958 --> 01:41:24.918
I can still hear her voice in my head.

01:41:30.340 --> 01:41:32.050
Even after she was hurt,

01:41:32.134 --> 01:41:34.344
she said to me
that we did the right thing.

01:41:43.645 --> 01:41:45.189
She told me that with great power...

01:41:47.357 --> 01:41:49.109
Comes great responsibility.

01:41:54.573 --> 01:41:55.991
Wait, what? How do you know that?

01:41:56.074 --> 01:41:57.618
Uncle Ben said it.

01:41:57.701 --> 01:41:59.161
The day he died.

01:42:03.874 --> 01:42:05.959
Maybe she didn't die for nothing, Peter.

01:42:16.053 --> 01:42:20.891
Okay, so Connors,
Marko, Dillon and, um...

01:42:22.184 --> 01:42:24.645
I think that I can repair
the devices for Dillon and Marko,

01:42:24.728 --> 01:42:25.938
but the others....

01:42:26.605 --> 01:42:29.816
Oh, I got Connors.
I've cured him once, so no big deal.

01:42:31.485 --> 01:42:33.362
-What? It's no big deal.
-Great.

01:42:34.238 --> 01:42:35.364
Yeah, that's great.

01:42:38.116 --> 01:42:40.911
I think I can make an antiserum
for Dr Osborn.

01:42:42.079 --> 01:42:43.872
Been thinking about it a long time.

01:42:47.000 --> 01:42:49.503
Gotta cure all of them. Right?

01:42:51.129 --> 01:42:51.964
Right.

01:42:53.715 --> 01:42:54.925
That's what we do.

01:42:59.847 --> 01:43:01.014
Psst.

01:43:03.392 --> 01:43:04.268
What?

01:43:04.935 --> 01:43:06.311
Just three yous.

01:43:22.494 --> 01:43:23.495
Um...

01:43:24.538 --> 01:43:27.583
So... do you have a best friend too?

01:43:30.002 --> 01:43:30.836
I did.

01:43:33.046 --> 01:43:34.006
You did?

01:43:35.883 --> 01:43:37.301
He died in my arms...

01:43:39.261 --> 01:43:40.804
after he tried to kill me.

01:43:42.848 --> 01:43:44.266
It was heart-breaking.

01:43:46.518 --> 01:43:47.603
Dude.

01:43:54.568 --> 01:43:57.029
-Hey.
-Will you run a diagnostic?

01:43:57.112 --> 01:43:57.946
Yeah.

01:44:07.581 --> 01:44:08.582
Hey, you okay?

01:44:10.167 --> 01:44:12.377
-Uh, yeah, I'm fine. Are you okay?
-Mm-hm.

01:44:15.881 --> 01:44:17.341
You don't deserve this.

01:44:18.800 --> 01:44:21.929
-I've ruined your life. I ruined it.
-No. No, no, no.

01:44:22.721 --> 01:44:24.556
Look at me. I'm here.

01:44:26.183 --> 01:44:27.351
Not going anywhere.

01:44:29.269 --> 01:44:32.272
We'll get through this
and we'll get through it together.

01:44:33.315 --> 01:44:34.149
Okay?

01:44:35.567 --> 01:44:37.528
-Okay.
-Okay.

01:44:42.616 --> 01:44:43.534
Thank you.

01:44:55.045 --> 01:44:56.463
You have someone?

01:44:57.297 --> 01:44:58.131
No.

01:44:59.091 --> 01:45:03.512
I got no time
for Peter Parker stuff, you know?

01:45:05.597 --> 01:45:07.516
-Do you?
-Uh...

01:45:08.225 --> 01:45:10.227
That's a little complicated.

01:45:11.228 --> 01:45:12.437
I understand.

01:45:12.521 --> 01:45:14.898
I guess it's just not
in the cards for guys like us.

01:45:14.982 --> 01:45:17.651
Well, I wouldn't give up.

01:45:17.734 --> 01:45:20.654
Took a while but we made it work.

01:45:20.737 --> 01:45:22.364
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

01:45:22.447 --> 01:45:25.158
Me and... MJ.

01:45:26.618 --> 01:45:28.745
My MJ. Uh...

01:45:29.663 --> 01:45:31.206
It gets confusing here.

01:45:31.290 --> 01:45:33.417
Yeah.

01:45:33.500 --> 01:45:35.502
- Peter!
- Yeah?

01:45:35.586 --> 01:45:39.006
- Oh, sorry, did you mean...?
- "Peter" Peter.

01:45:39.089 --> 01:45:40.924
-We're all called Peter.
-We're all Peter.

01:45:41.008 --> 01:45:44.052
-Peter Parker?
-Same again. We're all Peter Parker.

01:45:44.136 --> 01:45:45.637
-The computer.
-Oh.

01:45:47.014 --> 01:45:48.557
- Oh, I'm ready.
- Yeah. Me too.

01:45:48.640 --> 01:45:53.562
Okay, so now, all we gotta do is lure
these guys someplace, right?

01:45:53.645 --> 01:45:57.149
Try to cure them
while they try to kill us,

01:45:57.232 --> 01:45:58.775
and then send them home.

01:45:58.859 --> 01:46:01.486
-Using a magic box.
-Well, that's the plan.

01:46:01.570 --> 01:46:04.072
Are you gonna go into battle
dressed as a cool youth pastor,

01:46:04.156 --> 01:46:05.741
or do you got your suit?

01:46:07.784 --> 01:46:08.619
Good.

01:46:08.702 --> 01:46:11.163
-Here's your web cartridges.
-Ah, thanks, man.

01:46:11.246 --> 01:46:12.456
What's that for?

01:46:12.539 --> 01:46:15.375
It's my web fluid.
It's for my web shooters. Why?

01:46:16.460 --> 01:46:17.878
Whoa!

01:46:18.712 --> 01:46:20.547
-That came out of you.
-Yeah.

01:46:20.631 --> 01:46:22.299
-You can't do that, huh?
-No.

01:46:22.382 --> 01:46:24.134
How on earth does that even--?

01:46:24.218 --> 01:46:26.970
We're getting side-tracked.
This is where we'll do this, okay?

01:46:27.054 --> 01:46:28.805
It's isolated, so no one should get hurt.

01:46:29.473 --> 01:46:31.975
We draw them there with the box.
It's the one thing they all want.

01:46:32.059 --> 01:46:34.186
All we have to do is figure out
how to get there.

01:46:34.269 --> 01:46:35.687
-We could portal there.
-What?

01:46:35.771 --> 01:46:38.190
-I'm magic now.
-Yeah, he's right. He can.

01:46:38.273 --> 01:46:39.942
-Yeah, we saw.
-Yeah, he is.

01:46:40.442 --> 01:46:42.319
-Wait, really?
-I got Doctor Strange magic.

01:46:42.402 --> 01:46:43.612
- No way.
- Yeah.

01:46:44.363 --> 01:46:47.783
I promise you, I won't turn
into a supervillain and try to kill you.

01:46:50.077 --> 01:46:51.161
Okay.

01:46:52.120 --> 01:46:53.372
Thank you.

01:46:58.043 --> 01:47:02.089
Um... here goes nothing.
What's that thing you always say?

01:47:02.798 --> 01:47:05.175
-Expect disappointment and--
-No, no, no.

01:47:06.552 --> 01:47:08.220
We're gonna kick some ass.

01:47:08.303 --> 01:47:09.304
Okay.

01:47:10.013 --> 01:47:12.474
Cure. Cure some ass.

01:47:12.558 --> 01:47:14.393
Cure that ass.

01:47:16.854 --> 01:47:18.313
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

01:47:18.397 --> 01:47:20.065
<i>the </i>Bugle<i> tip line has
just received a call</i>

01:47:20.148 --> 01:47:23.402
<i>from none other
than the fugitive known as Spider-Man,</i>

01:47:23.485 --> 01:47:25.946
<i>fresh from his rampage in Queens.</i>

01:47:26.697 --> 01:47:30.826
<i>So, Peter Parker, what pernicious
propaganda are you peddling?</i>

01:47:30.909 --> 01:47:33.829
- <i>Just the truth. Truth is...
- </i>-<i>Oh, sure.</i>

01:47:35.372 --> 01:47:37.583
<i>-that this is all my fault.</i>

01:47:37.666 --> 01:47:40.210
<i>I accidentally brought
those dangerous people here.</i>

01:47:40.294 --> 01:47:41.962
Well, he admits it.

01:47:42.045 --> 01:47:43.589
<i>And if those people are watching...</i>

01:47:45.632 --> 01:47:47.509
<i>just know that I did try to help you.</i>

01:47:48.886 --> 01:47:50.429
<i>I could have killed you...</i>

01:47:51.722 --> 01:47:53.849
<i>at any given moment, but I didn't.</i>

01:47:56.018 --> 01:47:59.146
<i>'Cause my Aunt May taught me
that everyone deserves a second chance.</i>

01:47:59.229 --> 01:48:02.107
<i>-That's why I'm here.
</i>-Where is "here," exactly?

01:48:04.067 --> 01:48:06.111
A place that represents second chances.

01:48:09.031 --> 01:48:11.783
<i>The Statue of Liberty?
Good God, folks.</i>

01:48:11.867 --> 01:48:15.120
<i>He's about to destroy
another national landmark.</i>

01:48:15.204 --> 01:48:16.872
World, if you're watching...

01:48:16.955 --> 01:48:18.790
<i>Believe me,
the world is watching.</i>

01:48:19.583 --> 01:48:20.709
...wish me luck.

01:48:22.669 --> 01:48:24.880
Your friendly neighbourhood Spider-Man
could use some.

01:48:31.428 --> 01:48:33.514
Okay, it could be any minute now.

01:48:33.597 --> 01:48:35.807
Yep, almost done.

01:48:40.729 --> 01:48:45.317
You know, Max was,
like, the sweetest guy ever

01:48:45.943 --> 01:48:47.277
before he fell into...

01:48:48.195 --> 01:48:52.783
-a pool of electric eels.
-That'll do it.

01:48:56.161 --> 01:48:58.830
All the things I wished
I could have done differently.

01:49:01.083 --> 01:49:03.043
Now to have a second chance.

01:49:04.336 --> 01:49:05.170
Yeah.

01:49:09.383 --> 01:49:11.343
Mm. Oh, there it goes.

01:49:13.470 --> 01:49:14.638
You okay?

01:49:14.721 --> 01:49:16.557
Oh, it's my back.

01:49:16.640 --> 01:49:19.935
It's kind of stiff
from all the swinging, I guess.

01:49:20.018 --> 01:49:22.187
-Yeah. No, I got a middle-back thing too.
-Really?

01:49:22.271 --> 01:49:24.398
Yeah. You want me to crack it?

01:49:25.691 --> 01:49:26.942
-Yeah.
-Yeah?

01:49:27.025 --> 01:49:28.443
-That'd be great.
-All right.

01:49:30.028 --> 01:49:31.113
-You ready?
-Yeah.

01:49:34.491 --> 01:49:36.034
Yep. That's good.

01:49:36.827 --> 01:49:38.662
-How is it?
-Wow.

01:49:40.247 --> 01:49:42.666
-That's good. That's better.
-Right? Yeah.

01:49:42.749 --> 01:49:43.584
Wow.

01:49:46.920 --> 01:49:49.756
This is so cool. I always wanted brothers.

01:49:50.841 --> 01:49:53.635
We should do this again,
like, all hang out.

01:49:53.719 --> 01:49:55.095
It's nice.

01:49:55.179 --> 01:49:58.015
We should maybe, you know, focus on...

01:49:58.098 --> 01:49:59.683
On not getting killed tonight.

01:49:59.766 --> 01:50:01.768
Yeah. For sure. That's a good idea.

01:50:01.852 --> 01:50:04.605
I'll just grab your number
at the end of the battle.

01:50:04.688 --> 01:50:06.190
You got it.

01:50:06.815 --> 01:50:09.860
So you, like,
make your own web fluid in your body?

01:50:09.943 --> 01:50:11.653
I'd rather not talk about this.

01:50:11.737 --> 01:50:13.697
-I don't mean to--
-But are you teasing me?

01:50:13.780 --> 01:50:17.618
No, no, no. He's not teasing you.
It's just that we can't do that,

01:50:17.701 --> 01:50:21.205
so we're curious as to how
your web situation works, that's all.

01:50:21.288 --> 01:50:23.999
If it's personal, I don't wanna pry,
but I think it's cool.

01:50:24.082 --> 01:50:27.169
I-- I wish I could tell you,
but it's, like, I don't do it.

01:50:27.252 --> 01:50:29.546
Like I don't do breathing.

01:50:29.630 --> 01:50:31.590
-Like, breathing just happens.
-Whoa.

01:50:31.965 --> 01:50:35.802
It's just, like, when it releases,
it's like a clean release.

01:50:35.886 --> 01:50:36.803
Can I ask something?

01:50:36.887 --> 01:50:38.096
-Yeah.
-Is it like:

01:50:38.180 --> 01:50:40.349
When you think it, it webs?

01:50:40.432 --> 01:50:42.184
That's a good way to put it.

01:50:42.267 --> 01:50:45.103
Because if I press...
I have to have a mechanism.

01:50:45.187 --> 01:50:48.982
-Right.
-But for you, is it like, "Web"?

01:50:49.066 --> 01:50:50.150
And then it webs?

01:50:50.234 --> 01:50:53.111
Uh, not even conscious at this point.

01:50:53.195 --> 01:50:54.947
It's just like riding a bike.

01:50:55.030 --> 01:50:59.368
Does it just come out of your wrists,
or does it come out of anywhere else?

01:50:59.451 --> 01:51:01.662
Only-- Only the wrists.

01:51:01.745 --> 01:51:03.956
Never had a web block?
I run out of webs all the time.

01:51:04.039 --> 01:51:06.542
- I have to make my own in a lab.
- Right. That's--

01:51:06.625 --> 01:51:09.586
-It's a hassle compared to what you got.
-Sounds like a hassle.

01:51:09.670 --> 01:51:13.131
But I did. You said that,
I was like, "Oh. I had a web block."

01:51:13.215 --> 01:51:15.717
-Whoa. Why?
-Existential-crisis stuff.

01:51:15.801 --> 01:51:18.470
Pfft. Yeah. Don't get me started on that.

01:51:18.554 --> 01:51:20.848
I'm not sure what to say.
It's just a natural thing.

01:51:20.931 --> 01:51:22.224
It just happens.

01:51:23.517 --> 01:51:24.351
I don't know.

01:51:24.434 --> 01:51:25.644
It's so cool, man.

01:51:25.727 --> 01:51:28.647
- Like, I wanna see the holes.
- Hey.

01:51:28.814 --> 01:51:31.900
What are some of the craziest villains
that you guys have fought?

01:51:31.984 --> 01:51:34.695
-Seems you've met some of them.
-That's a good question.

01:51:34.778 --> 01:51:40.117
Yeah, I fought an alien
made out of black goo once.

01:51:40.200 --> 01:51:42.286
Oh, no way. I fought an alien too.

01:51:42.369 --> 01:51:44.079
-On Earth and in space.
-Oh.

01:51:44.162 --> 01:51:45.956
-He was purple.
-I wanna fight an alien.

01:51:46.039 --> 01:51:49.793
I'm still, like, that you fought
an alien in space.

01:51:50.669 --> 01:51:54.631
I'm always simultaneously,
like, completely stunned

01:51:55.215 --> 01:51:59.052
by the fantastical nature of these things,

01:51:59.136 --> 01:52:01.972
and it's also just like,
"Yeah. Okay. Yeah."

01:52:02.055 --> 01:52:03.765
Yeah, it's Monday. Yeah.

01:52:03.849 --> 01:52:04.850
I mean--

01:52:05.475 --> 01:52:09.688
I'm lame compared-- I fought
a Russian guy in a rhinoceros machine.

01:52:10.105 --> 01:52:10.981
That's cool.

01:52:11.064 --> 01:52:12.649
Not as-- No, it's not.

01:52:12.733 --> 01:52:15.444
Can we rewind it back
to the "I'm lame" part?

01:52:15.527 --> 01:52:16.403
'Cause you are not.

01:52:16.486 --> 01:52:18.572
Thanks. I appreciate that.
I'm not saying I am--

01:52:18.655 --> 01:52:20.616
But it's just the self-talk.
Maybe we should...

01:52:20.699 --> 01:52:23.452
- Listen, I--
- 'Cause you're amazing.

01:52:23.535 --> 01:52:25.454
Just to take it in for a minute.

01:52:25.537 --> 01:52:28.040
- Yeah, I can take it in.
- You are amazing.

01:52:28.123 --> 01:52:30.709
-I can. Thank you.
-You are amazing. Will you say it?

01:52:30.792 --> 01:52:32.336
I needed to hear that. Thank you.

01:52:33.670 --> 01:52:35.881
All right, guys, focus up. You feel that?

01:52:35.964 --> 01:52:36.798
Yeah.

01:52:44.389 --> 01:52:45.474
What's up, Peter?

01:52:48.560 --> 01:52:50.062
How you like the new-new?

01:52:51.230 --> 01:52:56.235
Look, you give it to me,
I'm gonna destroy it.

01:52:56.318 --> 01:52:57.736
But I'll let you live.

01:52:58.403 --> 01:52:59.947
Don't make me a murderer, Peter.

01:53:02.824 --> 01:53:04.451
Okay, guys, here he comes.

01:53:11.166 --> 01:53:14.795
Hey, Max!
I missed you, man. Ho!

01:53:16.755 --> 01:53:18.298
All right, MJ, heads up!

01:53:19.341 --> 01:53:20.509
Got it! Close it.

01:53:24.555 --> 01:53:26.640
-Ned, it's not closing.
-Yeah, I know.

01:53:26.723 --> 01:53:28.308
-Why isn't it closing?
-I don't know.

01:53:28.392 --> 01:53:31.436
-Did you close it before? No?
-I mean, I've opened some.

01:53:40.362 --> 01:53:42.781
Max, Max, Max. Can we talk for a second?

01:53:42.865 --> 01:53:44.950
-Just you and me, just talk?
-Look who showed up.

01:53:45.659 --> 01:53:46.952
My old friend Spider-Man.

01:53:47.035 --> 01:53:48.996
I'm trying to save you.
That's all I've wanted.

01:53:49.079 --> 01:53:50.664
-You're not trying to save me.
-I am.

01:53:50.747 --> 01:53:52.541
You ain't even the shit no more.

01:53:52.624 --> 01:53:55.961
-Oh.
-Don't worry about me. I'll save myself.

01:53:56.670 --> 01:53:59.381
- Burn up!
- Oh!

01:53:59.464 --> 01:54:01.091
Well, I got his attention. Now what?

01:54:01.175 --> 01:54:02.676
Okay, great.

01:54:03.427 --> 01:54:06.430
Uh, just FYI, lizard guy's here too.

01:54:08.140 --> 01:54:09.558
Guys, comm check. Hello?

01:54:10.767 --> 01:54:13.353
- <i>I need Max's cure!
</i>-Yeah. I'm on it.

01:54:14.313 --> 01:54:16.315
<i>Peter, I need the Lizard cure.</i>

01:54:16.398 --> 01:54:17.691
Okay, okay.

01:54:23.030 --> 01:54:24.740
Where's the box, Peter?

01:54:24.823 --> 01:54:27.618
-Flint, we could help everyone.
-I don't care!

01:54:39.004 --> 01:54:39.880
Sorry!

01:54:40.714 --> 01:54:41.924
Ugh. Gross!

01:54:42.633 --> 01:54:45.302
Sad to tell you, Sandman,
nobody's going home.

01:55:23.048 --> 01:55:26.051
Oh! What the hell is going on out there?

01:55:26.134 --> 01:55:27.886
I keep yelling at you, Peter 2!

01:55:27.970 --> 01:55:31.098
-But I thought you were Peter 2.
-What? I'm not Peter 2.

01:55:31.181 --> 01:55:33.433
Stop arguing, both of you!
Listen to Peter 1.

01:55:33.517 --> 01:55:36.436
-We're clearly not very good at this.
-I know, I know. We suck.

01:55:36.520 --> 01:55:39.356
-I don't know how to work as a team.
-Me neither.

01:55:39.439 --> 01:55:41.400
I do. I've been in a team, okay?

01:55:41.483 --> 01:55:44.111
I don't wanna brag, but I will.
I was in the Avengers.

01:55:44.194 --> 01:55:45.529
-The Avengers?
-Yeah.

01:55:45.612 --> 01:55:46.822
-That's great.
-Thank you.

01:55:46.905 --> 01:55:47.781
What is that?

01:55:48.949 --> 01:55:50.158
You don't have the Avengers?

01:55:50.242 --> 01:55:51.743
Is that a band? Are you in a band?

01:55:51.827 --> 01:55:55.205
No, I'm not in a band.
The Avengers is Earth's mightiest--

01:55:55.289 --> 01:55:57.040
-How's this helping?
-It's not important.

01:55:57.124 --> 01:55:58.959
All we gotta do is focus,
trust your tingle,

01:55:59.042 --> 01:56:00.460
and coordinate our attacks.

01:56:00.544 --> 01:56:03.255
Yes. Okay. Let's pick one target.

01:56:03.338 --> 01:56:05.716
-Right.
-We take them off the board one at a time.

01:56:05.799 --> 01:56:08.385
-You got it. Okay, Peter 1, Peter 2.
-Peter 2.

01:56:08.468 --> 01:56:09.761
-Peter 3.
-Peter 3.

01:56:09.845 --> 01:56:11.763
- Let's do this. Ready?
- Wait, wait!

01:56:12.723 --> 01:56:13.932
I love you guys.

01:56:16.602 --> 01:56:17.728
Thank you.

01:56:19.354 --> 01:56:20.898
-All right, let's do this.
-Let's go.

01:56:50.844 --> 01:56:54.348
Okay, Spider-Mans.
Sandman's first.

01:56:55.516 --> 01:56:58.352
-I'm gonna lead him inside the statue.
-I'll meet you at the top.

01:57:01.313 --> 01:57:03.148
- Come on!
- Hey!

01:57:06.109 --> 01:57:08.987
-Hey, Dr Connors.
-Hello, Peter.

01:57:10.280 --> 01:57:11.490
Peter 1!

01:57:11.573 --> 01:57:12.449
I got it!

01:57:24.169 --> 01:57:26.630
Flint, we're trying to help you!

01:57:28.715 --> 01:57:30.384
Guys, I'm at the top!

01:57:30.467 --> 01:57:34.054
I need the cure!

01:57:34.137 --> 01:57:35.681
I'm coming, I'm coming, I'm coming.

01:57:36.640 --> 01:57:41.478
Just wait your turn, doc!

01:57:41.562 --> 01:57:42.688
I'll be right back.

01:58:19.933 --> 01:58:21.143
It's okay, Flint.

01:58:23.395 --> 01:58:25.022
We're gonna get you home.

01:58:25.814 --> 01:58:27.733
You just stay right here.

01:58:32.362 --> 01:58:34.990
How do we stop him?
I've never seen him this powerful.

01:58:35.073 --> 01:58:37.367
It's the arc reactor.
We gotta get it off him.

01:58:37.451 --> 01:58:39.369
You're not gonna take this from me.

01:58:41.955 --> 01:58:42.915
That's not gonna work.

01:58:48.170 --> 01:58:49.796
We gotta do this up close.

01:58:49.880 --> 01:58:52.716
Peter 2, go right.
Peter 3, go left. On me.

01:58:57.763 --> 01:58:58.597
Yeah!

01:59:19.326 --> 01:59:20.202
Um...

01:59:20.285 --> 01:59:23.413
I'm trying to close it.
I can't help that it's not working.

01:59:23.497 --> 01:59:26.333
It's fine. You'll do it again.
We'll keep trying.

01:59:26.416 --> 01:59:29.545
-All right, we got this. Shh.
-Focus and close the portal.

01:59:32.881 --> 01:59:34.633
Oh, no. No, no, no.

01:59:34.716 --> 01:59:37.261
And that is a lizard and we should go!

01:59:41.807 --> 01:59:42.683
Run!

01:59:43.684 --> 01:59:46.144
Come on! Come on, this way!
Quick, quick, quick!

01:59:46.228 --> 01:59:47.604
Connors, stop!

01:59:54.987 --> 01:59:57.990
Yeah.

02:00:10.460 --> 02:00:13.005
Leave them. They're mine.

02:00:13.088 --> 02:00:15.674
I don't need your help.
I got it just fine.

02:00:15.757 --> 02:00:17.926
Dr Octavius, no.

02:00:20.512 --> 02:00:21.889
What are you doing?

02:00:23.557 --> 02:00:24.766
Get it off of me.

02:00:35.736 --> 02:00:36.862
There you go.

02:00:56.089 --> 02:00:56.965
MJ!

02:01:07.601 --> 02:01:08.769
Whoa.

02:01:09.353 --> 02:01:11.104
-We gotta hide this thing.
-Oh, right.

02:01:15.359 --> 02:01:16.985
-Nice, Ned!
-Yeah!

02:01:18.237 --> 02:01:19.071
Oh.

02:01:20.656 --> 02:01:21.573
Where is he?

02:01:21.657 --> 02:01:23.200
- No!
- Wait, wait, wait.

02:01:23.283 --> 02:01:27.329
Before you do anything, Mister--
Doctor Strange, Peter's plan is working.

02:01:27.412 --> 02:01:29.164
-What plan?
-He's curing them.

02:01:38.215 --> 02:01:39.341
Dr Connors?

02:01:42.761 --> 02:01:43.846
Welcome back, sir.

02:01:45.931 --> 02:01:47.182
Well, I'll be damned.

02:01:50.143 --> 02:01:51.770
Did you just open a portal?

02:01:52.771 --> 02:01:53.939
Yes, sir, I did.

02:01:54.731 --> 02:01:55.983
Hmm.

02:02:01.697 --> 02:02:04.783
Max? Max?

02:02:05.534 --> 02:02:08.662
-Don't worry. I'm all tapped out.
-Are you sure about that?

02:02:10.622 --> 02:02:11.915
Back to being a nobody.

02:02:11.999 --> 02:02:15.294
-You were never a nobody, Max.
-Yes, I was.

02:02:15.919 --> 02:02:18.005
You didn't see me.

02:02:18.547 --> 02:02:21.216
- Can I tell you something, though?
- Yeah.

02:02:22.259 --> 02:02:24.011
You got a nice face. You're just a kid.

02:02:25.012 --> 02:02:26.680
-Eh.
-You're from Queens.

02:02:27.806 --> 02:02:31.059
You got that suit.
You help a lot of poor people.

02:02:31.143 --> 02:02:32.978
I just thought you was gonna be Black.

02:02:34.188 --> 02:02:36.565
-Oh, man, I'm sorry.
-Don't apologise.

02:02:36.648 --> 02:02:39.067
There's gotta be a Black Spider-Man
somewhere out there.

02:02:42.529 --> 02:02:43.739
Goddamn eels.

02:02:47.492 --> 02:02:48.911
The power of the sun.

02:02:52.080 --> 02:02:54.958
- In the palm of your hand.
- Peter?

02:02:57.544 --> 02:02:58.378
Otto.

02:03:00.339 --> 02:03:02.132
Oh, it's good to see you, dear boy.

02:03:02.966 --> 02:03:04.343
It's good to see you.

02:03:05.135 --> 02:03:06.345
You're all grown up.

02:03:08.096 --> 02:03:09.139
How are you?

02:03:11.433 --> 02:03:12.476
Trying to do better.

02:03:19.900 --> 02:03:21.777
-Strange, wait, we're so close.
-Skip it!

02:03:21.860 --> 02:03:24.655
I've been dangling
over the Grand Canyon for 12 hours.

02:03:24.738 --> 02:03:27.824
I know, I know, I know.
I, uh-- Um...

02:03:28.659 --> 02:03:30.494
I'm sorry about that, sir. I mean...

02:03:30.577 --> 02:03:33.580
-You went to the Grand Canyon?
-He could have used your help.

02:03:33.664 --> 02:03:35.832
It's okay.
These are my new friends.

02:03:35.916 --> 02:03:38.377
This is Peter Parker, Peter Parker.
Spider-Man, Spider-Man.

02:03:38.460 --> 02:03:40.045
-They're mes from other universes.
-Oh.

02:03:40.128 --> 02:03:42.881
They're here to help.
This is the wizard I told you about.

02:03:42.965 --> 02:03:46.301
I am really impressed that you've managed
to give them all a second chance, kid.

02:03:47.511 --> 02:03:49.638
But this has to end. Now.

02:03:49.721 --> 02:03:53.100
Can the Spider-Man come out to play?

02:04:15.038 --> 02:04:16.248
Strange, no!

02:04:45.527 --> 02:04:46.737
Are you okay?

02:04:47.821 --> 02:04:48.697
Yeah.

02:04:48.780 --> 02:04:49.948
I'm okay.

02:04:52.951 --> 02:04:54.077
Are you okay?

02:05:10.093 --> 02:05:12.346
Whoa.

02:06:11.613 --> 02:06:13.115
Thank you, Mr Cape, sir.

02:06:16.451 --> 02:06:17.286
Ned?

02:06:18.704 --> 02:06:19.746
-Ned!
-Hey!

02:06:24.376 --> 02:06:25.294
MJ!

02:06:25.377 --> 02:06:26.545
Peter?

02:06:26.628 --> 02:06:28.463
- Ned!
- Peter!

02:06:29.339 --> 02:06:30.507
Hey!

02:06:30.591 --> 02:06:32.634
- Are you okay?
- We're okay!

02:06:46.773 --> 02:06:52.279
Poor Peter.
Too weak to send me home to die.

02:06:53.030 --> 02:06:53.864
No.

02:06:54.740 --> 02:06:56.450
I just wanna kill you myself.

02:06:57.284 --> 02:06:58.118
Attaboy.

02:08:48.478 --> 02:08:50.105
She was there...

02:08:50.814 --> 02:08:52.816
because of you.

02:08:52.900 --> 02:08:55.152
I may have struck the blow,

02:08:56.069 --> 02:08:57.487
but you...

02:09:00.908 --> 02:09:04.119
You are the one that killed her.

02:09:31.063 --> 02:09:31.897
Peter.

02:09:45.536 --> 02:09:46.745
What have I done?

02:09:50.832 --> 02:09:52.668
- It's you.
- You okay?

02:09:52.751 --> 02:09:55.879
Uh... Yeah, I'm good.
I've been stabbed before.

02:09:55.963 --> 02:09:57.589
-Oh, good, good, good.
-Hey.

02:09:57.673 --> 02:10:00.050
-Oh, man.
-Hey, nice catch.

02:10:01.176 --> 02:10:02.052
Nice throw.

02:10:04.680 --> 02:10:08.475
- What? Is that happening, or am I dying?
- Yeah, no, that's happening.

02:10:08.559 --> 02:10:10.894
- That's real.
- Are there people in the sky?

02:10:19.611 --> 02:10:21.864
-I gotta go.
-Yeah. I got it. You okay?

02:10:26.368 --> 02:10:27.661
What's happening?

02:10:27.744 --> 02:10:29.955
They're starting to come through.
I can't stop them.

02:10:30.038 --> 02:10:33.083
There's gotta be something we could do.
Can't you just cast the spell again?

02:10:33.166 --> 02:10:34.918
The original way, before I screwed it up.

02:10:35.002 --> 02:10:36.920
We're too late for that.
They're here.

02:10:37.838 --> 02:10:39.882
They're here because of you.

02:10:45.345 --> 02:10:46.847
What if everyone forgot who I was?

02:10:46.930 --> 02:10:47.806
What?

02:10:48.307 --> 02:10:51.226
They're coming here because of me, right?
Because I'm Peter Parker?

02:10:51.810 --> 02:10:52.978
So cast a new spell.

02:10:53.061 --> 02:10:55.480
But this time, make everyone forget
who Peter Parker is.

02:10:55.564 --> 02:10:56.940
Make everyone forget...

02:10:58.901 --> 02:11:00.319
-me.
-No.

02:11:00.402 --> 02:11:03.197
-But it would work, right?
-Yeah, it would work.

02:11:04.615 --> 02:11:07.201
But you gotta understand
that would mean that everyone

02:11:07.284 --> 02:11:09.828
who knows and loves you, we...

02:11:11.997 --> 02:11:13.874
We'd have no memory of you.

02:11:15.667 --> 02:11:17.503
It would be as though you never existed.

02:11:20.881 --> 02:11:21.715
I know.

02:11:23.759 --> 02:11:25.052
Do it.

02:11:28.680 --> 02:11:31.350
You better go and say your goodbyes.
You don't have long.

02:11:31.975 --> 02:11:34.019
-Thank you, sir.
-Call me Stephen.

02:11:37.689 --> 02:11:38.565
Thank you, Stephen.

02:11:40.609 --> 02:11:43.403
Yeah. Still feels weird.

02:11:46.073 --> 02:11:47.366
I'll see you around.

02:11:49.201 --> 02:11:50.244
So long, kid.

02:11:58.252 --> 02:11:59.586
Hey. Uh...

02:12:00.212 --> 02:12:02.756
I think this is it.
I think you're about to go home.

02:12:02.840 --> 02:12:04.341
-Okay.
-All right.

02:12:04.424 --> 02:12:06.301
Look, I, uh...

02:12:07.845 --> 02:12:08.846
Thank you.

02:12:09.763 --> 02:12:12.891
I just wanna-- I want you to--
I wanna tell you that--

02:12:13.600 --> 02:12:15.561
I don't know how to say this. I--

02:12:15.644 --> 02:12:17.312
-Peter.
-I want you to know that I...

02:12:19.022 --> 02:12:21.525
You know. It's what we do.

02:12:23.402 --> 02:12:25.529
Yeah, it's what we do. Um...

02:12:26.321 --> 02:12:28.782
Right, I gotta find Ned and MJ. I--

02:12:28.866 --> 02:12:32.286
Uh...
Thank you, thank you, thank you.

02:12:36.665 --> 02:12:39.168
- I guess I'll see you.
- See you.

02:12:39.251 --> 02:12:40.127
Bye.

02:12:42.754 --> 02:12:44.631
-Oh.
-You're in so much pain, huh?

02:12:44.715 --> 02:12:45.841
-I am.
-Yeah.

02:12:49.928 --> 02:12:51.972
Oh, you're okay.

02:12:52.931 --> 02:12:54.057
So proud of you.

02:12:55.142 --> 02:12:57.477
-Are you okay?
-Yeah, we're okay.

02:12:57.561 --> 02:12:59.980
-Oh, my God, you're bleeding.
-I'm fine. I'm okay.

02:13:00.063 --> 02:13:01.481
-You sure?
-I'm fine, I promise.

02:13:02.149 --> 02:13:03.400
- Okay, okay.
- I promise.

02:13:03.483 --> 02:13:04.318
Good.

02:13:05.903 --> 02:13:08.197
Um, we should go, right?

02:13:10.741 --> 02:13:13.535
Yeah. You're gonna forget who I am.

02:13:15.537 --> 02:13:17.831
-What?
-Forget? What are you talking about?

02:13:19.249 --> 02:13:23.962
It's okay. I'm gonna come and find you,
and I'll explain everything.

02:13:25.881 --> 02:13:27.424
I'll make you remember me.

02:13:28.258 --> 02:13:31.345
And it'll be like none of this
ever happened. Okay?

02:13:31.428 --> 02:13:34.765
But what if that doesn't work?
What if that doesn't work?

02:13:34.848 --> 02:13:37.226
What if we can't remember you?
I don't wanna do that.

02:13:37.976 --> 02:13:40.854
- I don't wanna do that.
- I know. MJ, I know.

02:13:40.938 --> 02:13:44.399
There's not something we can do?
We can't come up with a plan?

02:13:44.483 --> 02:13:45.984
There's always something we can do.

02:13:48.111 --> 02:13:49.321
There's nothing we can do.

02:13:53.951 --> 02:13:55.035
But it'll be okay.

02:13:59.540 --> 02:14:00.374
You promise?

02:14:03.544 --> 02:14:04.837
Yeah, I promise.

02:14:16.265 --> 02:14:17.766
I'll come find you, okay?

02:14:18.392 --> 02:14:19.643
I know you will.

02:14:21.144 --> 02:14:22.229
- Okay.
- Okay.

02:14:24.648 --> 02:14:25.941
You better.

02:14:27.901 --> 02:14:31.697
If you don't, I'll just figure it out.
I've done it before, I can do it again.

02:14:33.407 --> 02:14:34.908
I promise, I'll fix this.

02:14:36.285 --> 02:14:37.536
I really hate magic.

02:14:39.246 --> 02:14:40.372
Yeah. Me too.

02:14:45.127 --> 02:14:46.211
I love you.

02:14:52.634 --> 02:14:54.052
-I love--
-Just wait.

02:14:55.262 --> 02:14:57.598
Wait and tell me when you see me again.

02:14:59.600 --> 02:15:00.434
Sure.

02:16:28.230 --> 02:16:29.064
